, \"JavaScript\", \"Programmering\", \"SQL\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Databaser\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:05:55','2025-06-30 14:05:55'),(93,4259430838,'Technical Project Engineer',2,'Hiller√∏d, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nWould you like to support a global production and develop and improve production processes? Can you coordinate across organizations and boarders? Are you stimulated by hands-on tasks in production?\n\nThen this is your call ‚Äì the world‚Äôs leading manufacturer of insulin are looking for you! Read more and apply for paving the road to the next step on your journey!\n\nThe position\n\nOur department, Component Capacity Expansion within FPMSAT (Finished Product Manufacturing Science & Technology), is looking to expand a team with a test and project engineer to facilitate smooth execution of production expansion projects- both large and small scale.\n\nYou will be part of a team of highly skilled engineers that support our global production network (Denmark/US/China/Europe). We handle improvements, upgrades, and expansion of production capacity with a global production perspective.\n\nOur core task is the global expansion and validation activities of the automated production machines which does the laser engraving (decoration) of components for injectable devices.\n\nYour tasks will among others be to:\n\n\n\nAct as technical project lead\nDrive and coordinate test activities and GMP documents\nCollaborate across many functional areas and with people from different backgrounds\n\n\n\n\nQualifications\n\nTo be successful in this role you don‚Äôt have to be a technical expert, but you should have technical understanding.\n\nWe are looking for someone that has a technical academic degree, within mechanics is a plus, proven engineering experience and good understand of GMP.\n\nYou are proficient in English, written and verbally.\n\nMoreover, to succeed in this role, it is an advantage but not a requirement to have knowledge in the following