dit CPR-nummer via CPR-registeret med henblik p√• identifikation af dig i forbindelse med rekrutteringsprocessen. Vi indhenter dit CPR-nummer, s√• vi sikkert kan fremsende relevante og n√∏dvendige dokumenter til dig via Digital Post.\n\nDet er vigtigt for os, at PET afspejler den mangfoldighed, som vi arbejder for. Derfor opfordrer vi alle interesserede, uanset k√∏n, alder, religion, seksualitet og etniske tilh√∏rsforhold til at s√∏ge stillingen.\n\nTr√¶d ind i en lukket verden, der √•bner nye d√∏re, hvor vi udvikler os, tr√¶ner og bygger videre p√• det, vi kan. Om vi udvikler nye systemer, analyserer data eller finjusterer fodstillingen til skydetr√¶ning, s√• er vi altid p√• t√¶erne. Det skaber gode muligheder for, at du kan rykke dig med os, vokse med opgaverne og √•bne nye d√∏re i dit arbejdsliv.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4253307962/','2025-06-24',9,NULL,'[\"Styresystemer\", \"Design af sikkerhedsarkitektur\", \"Fejlfinding\", \"IT-ledelse\", \"Informationssikkerhed\", \"Informationsteknologi\", \"Opbygning af relationer\", \"Samarbejde\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:06:38','2025-06-30 14:06:38'),(97,4094722861,'Cloud Developer',51,'K√∏benhavns Kommune, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nAre you either experienced or graduate with some experience within Cloud Operations? If yes, don¬¥t hold back with applying. We are on an exciting journey to elevate cloud infrastructure to new heights in a dynamic scale-up environment that helps to revolutionize the worlds third biggest industry.\n\nYour new role \n\nWe are looking for a Cloud Developer to take our cloud operations to the next level. In this role, you will be at the forefront of ensuring the stability, scalability, and performance of our AWS infrastructure. Your expertise will be key to maintaining high availability and driving efficiency across our systems.\n\nResponsibilities: \n\n\nMonitor and improve the availability and performance of AWS cloud systems \nSet up and respond to on-call alerts to ensure smooth operations \nWork with Infrastructure as Code to maintain and evolve cloud resources \nManage application releases and patches by following clear processes\n\n\nYour background \n\nWe expect that you have a technical educational background. In addition, you have either experience as Cloud Developer or similar and see it as your strongest asset or tried it a bit and are willing to learn it more deeply ‚Äì we have open positions for both options.\n\nNeed to have skills: \n\n\nAWS Ecosystem Some experience with core AWS services including EC2, RDS, S3, CloudWatch, and CloudFormation\nDevelopment Have strong experience with C# and .NET in backend services and automation. \nInfrastructure as Code Experience with AWS CDK (or similar) and IaC best practices for scalable cloud deployments\nMonitoring & Alert Management Experience with PagerDuty (or similar) and implementing effective on-call response workflows\n\n\nNice to have skills: \n\n\nObservability Working knowledge of Elastic APM and application performance monitoring solutions \nDatabase Expertise MS SQL performance tuning skills including query optimization and execution plan analysis \nServer Administration Experience managing Windows Server environments in cloud contexts \n\n\nWhat To Expect As a Daluxian \n\nOur flat organization, where the way from idea to product is short combined with creative freedom and a high level of trust in your work, ensures that you will be able to create tangible value for our users. \n\nEveryday life is characterized by working onsite and sparring between colleagues, room to be yourself, monthly social events, and various clubs to mix professional development with fun. \n\nAs Dalux is a software company, we want half of the company to consist of Software Developers. All our software development happens at our head office at Vibenshuset in Copenhagen. \n\nReady for the next step \n\nIf the description above and Dalux sounds like a place where you could develop and contribute to high-quality software, we would gladly accept your application. We will be having ongoing interviews. \n\nIf you have any questions feel free to contact IT Talent Acquisition Specialist, Nicole Przybylski at np@dalux.com \n\nWho Is Dalux \n\nDalux is a Danish software company founded in 2005 by Ph.D. Bent Dalgaard and Torben Dalgaard. Dalux‚Äô products are aimed at making the construction industry smarter and more effective. Our user-friendly digital tools and Building Information Modelling-technology (also known as BIM) are used in more than 140 countries globally. \n\nWe are crazy about cool technology and have experience being first movers on new tech. Our products are based on our unique 3D BIM-technology and make use of AR - all developed entirely by Dalux.\n\nApplication deadline:\n\nAs soon as possible','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4094722861/','2025-06-23',100,NULL,'[\"Amazon EC2\", \"Amazon S3\", \"Cloud computing\", \"Google Cloud Platform (GCP)\", \"Infrastructure as code (IaC)\", \"Kubernetes\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\", \"AWS CloudFormation\", \"Amazon CloudWatch\", \"Pr√¶stationsjustering\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:06:38','2025-06-30 14:06:38'),(98,4255720434,'Migreringskonsulent',57,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nI Modern Work er vi passionerede for at skabe fremtidens digitale arbejdspladser, som g√∏r en forskel for vores kunder. Derfor har vi brug for flere kollegaer, som vil v√¶re med p√• denne rejse ‚Äì og vi h√•ber, at det kunne v√¶re dig!\n\nOm teamet\n\nI Modern Work besk√¶ftiger vi os med den digitale arbejdsplads og is√¶r den transformation og forandring, der skal ske med b√•de teknologi og mennesker. Vi leverer l√∏sninger, der integrerer og binder en organisation sammen ved at forbedre kommunikations- og samarbejdsprocesser samt vidensdelingen hos vores kunder. \n\nDu bliver en del af vores dedikerede migreringsteam best√•ende af 6 engagerede kolleger. Vi har et st√¶rkt samarbejde, hvor videndeling,