nOur culture is built on start-up energy, co-creation, creativity, and putting people first. It\'s not working in independent silos or crazy work hours (like some think). Instead, it‚Äôs a daily passion for the products we scale, verbal ping-pong at the office, and being in touch with your coworkers\n\nReady to be a key marketing player in our continued growth story? Read on to learn more.\n\nAbout Your Role\n\nAs our Growth Lead, you\'ll work closely with the CEO, taking charge of marketing and optimizing our funnelling process to significantly grow annual recurring revenue from subscriptions. It will require you to learn the entire funnelling process of the business and asses where your resources has the highest impact. You will be given freedom and responsibility to prioritize a big fraction of our budget between many running processes and new initiatives.\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\n\nTake the lead on growing the organisation‚Äôs revenue through marketing. You\'ll evaluate current processes and test new initiatives that you believe can further accelerate our organization‚Äôs growth.\nOwn & refine our SaaS funneling process. You\'ll analyze our entire freemium funnel to identify strategies for optimal resource allocation to grow revenue. This covers everything from traffic acquisition, retention, conversion, churn, and resurrection. The goal is to convert our 500k+ monthly free users into loyal subscribers and, crucially, retain them.\nDrive a data-powered traffic acquisition strategy. You‚Äôll be looking at various user data sources to optimize the marketing strategies. That includes looking into data from different platforms (social media, Google Analytics, website data), as well as collaborating with our user researchers to drive hypothesis testing and segmentation.\nOptimize Marketing Spend. You\'ll continuously evaluate how to best spend marketing resources. With a substantial marketing budget allocated, you\'ll compare the impact of new initiatives and current campaigns, carefully looking at metrics like ROI, website visits, conversion rates, and more.\nLead product-led growth. As part of a product team, you\'ll share how we can improve product-led growth. Your input will help shape the product into a sustainable service and inspire designs for a better funneling process.\nManage marketing processes & partners. You\'ll work with multiple consultants and partners who create content based on your strategies, analysis, and the EasySBC brand. This includes social media marketing, articles for SEO, paid ads on social, and coordinating with influencers and top e-sports athletes.\n\n\nWhat We Are Looking For\n\n\n1-3 years of experience analyzing and optimizing entire funneling processes.\n1-3 years of experience in subscription business, preferably B2C.\nExperience with different marketing disciplines like SoMe, SEO, paid ads, and influencer marketing.\nProficient in data analysis and BI tools‚Äîto turn complex data into strategies and actionable insights.\nAdaptable and confident working across different teams, tools, and product types.\nSkilled communicator with the ability to coordinate with partners, and a motivation for leading employees in the future.\nStart-up energy and a DO‚Äôer mentality‚Äîsomeone who can roll up their sleeves and execute.\n\n\nIdeally, you also have\n\n\nExperience with SaaS or freemium businesses\nUnderstanding of gaming communities\nUnderstanding of EA FC Ultimate Team and Football.\nExperience with branding.\nExperience with scale-ups or start-ups.\n\n\nWhy Join Us\n\nJoining us is a unique opportunity for you to:\n\nBecome part of something big: Get the chance to get warrants in an organically grown, profitable startup. We have built a spaceship with incredible momentum, and you can be the one to help us reach the stars - cheesy, but true.\n\nBe the driving force behind growth. Your work will impact millions of people from day one. If you‚Äôve dreamed of an opportunity to show your skills, this is your chance - backed by quality engineers and top-industry advisors in business development, marketing, and leadership.\n\nWork alongside passionate people in a great environment: Enjoy the office rooftop, indoor ball court, delicious lunch, and working with people passionate about the product, and scaling it beyond the skies.\n\nIf you\'re ready to make a significant impact and grow with a company that\'s already soaring, we want to hear from you.\n\nDetails\n\nüìù Type: Full Time, On-Site\n\nüí∞ Salary: Competitive w/ Warrants\n\nüìç Location: N√∏rrebro, Copenhagen\n\n‚è∞ Deadline: 7th of July 2025','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4251189473/','2025-06-23',NULL,NULL,'[\"Analytiske kompetencer\", \"Annoncering\", \"Campaigns\", \"Digital marketing\", \"Google Analytics\", \"Marketing\", \"Marketing Budget Management\", \"S√∏gemaskineoptimering (SEO)\", \"Tildeling af resourser\", \"Webanalyse\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:07:20','2025-06-30 14:07:20'),(107,4259435298,'Project Lead - Digital and Procurement Transformation',2,'Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nAre you motivated by the opportunity to lead strategic project(s) driving digital transformation and streamlining Source to Pay (S2P) and procurement processes within a global organization? Do you have a deep understanding of the upstream and downstream procurement, accounts payable processes and setup, system landscape, and tools such as Coupa and SAP? Are you enthusiastic about making a significant impact on Novo Nordisk\'s global S2P operating model?\n\nIf so, this role could be an ideal fit for you!\n\nThe position\n\nAs the Project Lead, you will be part of the Advanced Technology department within Procurement Excellence, a Center of Excellence (CoE) focused on optimizing the source to pay process through the utilization of innovative technology. This role offers a unique opportunity to leverage your project management expertise to drive change, lead digital innovative solutions, and gain exposure within a global organization during a time where procurement excellence is a key priority on the corporate agenda.\n\nCurrently, we are undertaking a thorough evaluation of the global P2P setup to evaluate its effectiveness across various aspects such as people, processes, and technology.\n\nIn this position, your responsibilities will include:\n\n\n\nLead the Project Management Office (PMO) for the project.\nOversee the implementation of short-term and long-term initiatives to address identified challenges.\nEnsure the establishment of a fit-for-purpose operating model enabled by smart technology.\n\n\n\n\nQualifications\n\nAs our ideal candidate, you should meet the following qualifications:\n\n\n\nHold a bachelor‚Äôs degree in economics, business administration, finance, engineering, supply chain management or related fields\nPossess minimum of 15 years of experience, preferably from a top-tier management consultancy or a leading global company operating across multiple locations\nHave a proven track record of leading the implementation of global IT systems and realising their values\nDemonstrate extensive knowledge of procurement and S2P systems (e.g., Coupa, SAP) and processes, particularly expertise in driving Purchase to Pay (P2P) standardisation \nExhibit excellent project management skills, with ability to lead complex projects involving diverse global stakeholders and multiple project streams simultaneously\nShowcase exceptional communication skills including interacting with and reporting to executive and senior management levels\nDemonstrate the ability to influence and guide diverse project teams effectively, particularly in the procurement field.\n\n\n\n\nOn a personal level, you are motivated by driving change, bridging gaps across cultures and effectively collaborating with stakeholders at all organisational levels. You set high ambitions for yourself and can motivate and lead others without authority. Moreover, you effectively multitask and manage multiple priorities in an organized manner. Lastly, you are analytical and result-oriented with excellent communication and presentation skills.\n\nAbout The Department\n\nCorporate Procurement is the Centre of Excellence for procurement in Novo Nordisk. We are responsible for the global procurement strategy, processes, and systems. We negotiate contracts covering more than DKK 80 billion of Novo Nordisk‚Äôs spend. Global Procurement has 500 employees around the world with the largest hubs in Denmark, India and the US.\n\nA key enabler for taking Procurement to the next level will be to leverage holistic insights to drive value in and from procurement. The Advanced Analytics team is responsible for driving this journey.\n\nWorking at Novo Nordisk\n\nNovo Nordisk is a leading global healthcare company with a 100-year legacy of driving change to defeat serious chronic diseases. Building on our strong legacy within diabetes, we are growing massively and expanding our commitment, reaching millions around the world and impacting more than 40 million patient lives daily. All of this has made us one of the 20 most valuable companies in the world by market cap. Our success relies on the joint potential and collaboration of our more than 63,000 employees around the world. We recognize the importance of the unique skills and perspectives our people bring to the table, and we work continuously to bring out the best in them. Working at Novo Nordisk, we\'re working toward something bigger than ourselves, and it\'s a collective effort. Join us! Together, we go further. Together, we\'re life-changing.\n\nContact \n\nFor further information, please contact the Senior Director of Advanced Technology, An Tran at ABQT@novonordisk.com.\n\nDeadline \n\n3rd August 2025\n\nYou do not need to attach a cover letter to your application, but please include a few sentences about why you are applying in your resume or CV. To ensure an efficient and fair recruitment process, please refrain from adding a photo in your CV. Applications will be handled as they are received, so please do not hesitate to apply.\n\nWe commit to an inclusive recruitment process and equality of opportunity for all our job applicants.\n\nAt Novo Nordisk we recognize that it is no longer good enough to aspire to be the best company in the world. We need to aspire to be the best company for the world and we know that this is only possible with talented employees with diverse perspectives, backgrounds and cultures. We are therefore committed to creating an inclusive culture that celebrates the diversity of our employees, the patients we serve and communities we operate in. Together, we‚Äôre life changing.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4259435298/','2025-06-30',NULL,NULL,'[\"Analytiske kompetencer\", \"Bridging Gaps\", \"Digital marketing\", \"Indk√∏b\", \"Kommunikation\", \"P2P\", \"PMO\", \"Projektteams\", \"Pr√¶sentationer\", \"Pr√¶sentationskompetencer\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:08:01','2025-06-30 14:08:01'),(108,4259421895,'Juleassistance til aften og weekender i BR - Greve',21,'Greve Strand, Region Sj√¶lland, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nJuleassistance til aften og weekend hos BR\n\nVil du v√¶re med p√• et st√¶rkt team, der hver eneste dag giver gode oplevelser og god vejledning? Er du energisk og entusiastisk, og kan du v√¶re med til at skabe en stemning, hvor vores kunder i alle aldre kan finde begejstring og inspiration blandt de kendte klassikere og de nyeste skud p√• leget√∏jsstammen?\n\nS√• har vi en sp√¶ndende mulighed til dig.\n\nHos BR skaber vi oplevelser, og du er en vigtig del af et team pr√¶get af samarbejde og fleksibilitet, hvor kunden og den gode vejledning og service er i centrum. Du bliver del af et hold af medarbejdere med en f√¶lles begejstring for leget√∏j og ikke mindst for legeb√∏rn. At skabe den gode kundeoplevelse hos BR er meget mere end at s√∏rge for fyldte hylder og en god bundlinje. Det er at evne at skabe den rette stemning, og det er at give kundern