er ansvar, leverer resultater, str√¶ber efter forbedringer og er en holdspiller.\n\nEr du klar til at sende din ans√∏gning afsted?\n\nHvis du stadig er nysgerrig p√• de mange muligheder f√∏tex kan tilbyde, og er klar til at give den fuld gas i f√∏tex‚Äô bl√• skjorte, s√• klik p√• linket nedenfor og lad os h√∏re mere om, hvem du er. Vi gl√¶der os meget til at h√∏re fra dig :)\n\nSalling Group er en mangfoldig arbejdsplads med 60.000 medarbejdere i Danmark, Tyskland og Polen.\n\nVi driver butikker, varehuse, cafeer, spisesteder og webshops med v√¶gt p√• kvalitet, service og omtanke for de samfund og den klode, vi er en del af.\n\nVi br√¶nder for at g√∏re hverdagen bedre for vores kunder','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4255118071/','2025-06-23',NULL,NULL,'[\"Coaching\", \"Events\", \"Kundeservice\", \"Probleml√∏sning\", \"Samarbejde\", \"Sociale medier\", \"Spil\", \"Team-koordinering\", \"Teamledelse\", \"Teamlederskab\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:08:01','2025-06-30 14:08:01'),(110,4219145213,'Computer Graphics Developer for Computer Vision Area',51,'K√∏benhavns Kommune, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nAre you passionate about advanced graphics and software development? Do you want to contribute to our machine learning solutions for the automatization of construction processes, with the goal of minimizing waste through digitalization?\n\nYour new role \n\nBringing data from offices to the construction site using 3D BIM models has long been part of our core expertise here at Dalux. Now, as one of the next steps in our effort to digitalize the construction industry, we are working to bring data from the construction site and back into the office using computer vision and machine learning technologies.\n\nAs a Computer Graphics Developer in our Computer Vision area, you will build new features and introduce new improvements to our existing platform, actively contributing to our software architecture and cross-team collaborations. As part of an R&D team, you will work on discovery of new solutions through research and rapid prototyping, delivering high quality solutions to complex computer vision problems, utilizing 3D models of the construction site and video data gathered using our vSLAM system.\n\nYour background \n\nWe believe you...\n\n\nHave a solid theoretical foundation from a bachelor‚Äôs degree in computer science, engineering, IT or similar. A master‚Äôs degree with specialization in visual computing is a plus. \nHave hands-on experience with software development using C++. \nExperienced in applying software engineering best practices to write clean, consistent and maintainable code. \nHave computer graphics experience or trained in the area. Hands-on experience with a computer graphics API is expected. Proficiency in Vulkan or OpenGL is a plus. \nHave interest in using machine learning for creative problem-solving. \nAre proactive, solution-oriented and able to work both independently and as part of a team. \n\n\nMost important is your problem-solving attitude, passion for software craftmanship, and the ambition to participate in the full lifecycle of our computer vision solutions for our products.\n\nOur tech \n\n\nC++ \nOpenGL \nImGui \nPython \nPyTorch \n\n\nWe are focused on using the right tools for the job, and as such the list of technologies may change depending on our needs and new offerings.\n\nWhat To Expect As a Daluxian\n\nAt Dalux, we foster a creative, collaborative, and supportive environment where your ideas make an impact. Here‚Äôs what you can look forward to as part of our team:\n\n\nCentral location in Copenhagen, focus on work/life balance without any overtime, and no dress code. \nAn active social environment with monthly events and social clubs. \nFlat communication in our organization, where the journey from idea to product is short combined with creative freedom and a high level of trust in your work, ensures that you will be able to create tangible value for our users. \nYou will join a highly specialized, international team with room for creativity and professional growth. \nStrong focus on diversity and inclusion ‚Äì your ideas are heard, and opportunities are available to all. \nAttractive employee benefits such as health insurance, lunch plan, coffee and fruit, free fitness facilities, and free parking garage. \nFocus on your development and well-being, with support for both professional goals and personal growth. \n\n\nReady for the next step \n\nIf Dalux sounds like a place where you could develop and contribute to the high-quality software, we would gladly accept your application. We will be having ongoing interviews.\n\nIf you have any questions, feel free to contact IT TAS, Simone Jena Berg Christensen, sch@dalux.com\n\nWho Is Dalux\n\nDalux is a Danish software company founded in 2005 by Ph.D. Bent Dalgaard and Torben Dalgaard. Dalux‚Äô products are aimed at making the construction industry smarter and more effective. Our user-friendly digital tools and Building Information Modelling-technology (also known as BIM) is used in more than 140 countries globally.\n\nWe are crazy about cool technology and have experience being first movers on new tech. Our products are based on our unique 3D BIM-technology and makes use of AR - all developed entirely by Dalux.\n\nApplication deadline:\n\nOngoing','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4219145213/','2025-06-23',87,NULL,'[\"C++\", \"Datalogi\", \"Computergrafik\", \"Computervision\", \"Grafik\", \"Iv√¶rks√¶tteri\", \"Kreativ probleml√∏sning\", \"Maskinl√¶ring\", \"OpenGL\", \"Probleml√∏sning\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:08:01','2025-06-30 14:08:01'),(111,4251185750,'Senior Backend Engineer',60,'K√∏benhavns Kommune, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nWe\'re a bootstrapped, profitable, and sustainable startup that\'s been building innovative, B2C products in Copenhagen for three years, founded by a team of six engineers. We\'ve proven our product-market fit, and now we\'re ready for our next big step: bringing on a Senior Backend Engineer to architect and build the robust, scalable systems that will support our growth and ambitious product roadmap.\n\nWe\'ve built a culture around startup energy, co-creation, and putting people first‚Äîthat means no silos or crazy hours. Instead, it\'s a daily passion for the products we\'re scaling and genuine connection with your coworkers.\n\nAs a Senior Backend Engineer in our start-up you\'ll own and evolve our backend architecture, ensuring optimal performance and scalability for our frontend and AI layers. You\'ll maintain and extend our backend APIs and architect and optimize our MongoDB data structures and queries. You will also build and maintain our AWS infrastructure with robust CI/CD pipelines, and collaborate closely with the rest of the product team.\n\nWhat You Will Bring\n\n\nA drive for building products that solve problems and bring value to users.\nA collaborative approach and a motivation for partnering across Product, Design and AI. \nA proactive mindset, thriving in an environment where you often define your own tasks and drive them to completion.\nA desire to be an integral part of refining our product roadmap and strategically deciding which features to implement alongside the product team.\n\n\nWhat You Will Be Doing\n\n\nBe part of a growing, fast paced startup where your work has immediate impact.\nOwn and evolve our backend architecture, from API design to database performance - serving both our frontend and AI-driven algorithmic layer.\nContinuously improve how we structure, store, and query data in MongoDB to optimize both speed and cost.\nHelp us scale up our AWS-based infrastructure setting up robust CI/CD pipelines and ensuring secure, seamless communication between services.\nCollaborate closely with our Product team, contributing to a high-performance, high-quality development culture through regular feedback and code reviews.\nBe a part of the ideation process with our AI & Data engineer for developing new algorithms.\n\n\nWhat You\'re Good At\n\n\nExcellent understanding of building and maintaining RESTful APIs using TypeScript (or similar backend languages).\nSignificant experience in designing NoSQL data models and writing complex queries, ideally in MongoDB or a similar database.\nHands-on experience scaling and maintaining AWS cloud infrastructure.\nSolid understanding of DevOps practices, including CI/CD pipelines (e.g. GitHub Actions), automated testing, and deployment workflows.\nComfortable working with algorithmic codebases and data processing logic (e.g. in Python or similar).\n\n\nIdeally you also have\n\n\nPrevious experience in a startup, scale-up, or small-team environment.\nDeep knowledge of MongoDB Atlas scaling strategies and advanced aggregation pipelines.\nFamiliarity with NestJS framework.\nExperience integrating Stripe Webhooks or similar payment systems.\nExperience with managing large scale serverless deployments such as AWS Lambda.\n\n\nDetails\n\nüìù Type: Full Time, On-Site\n\nüí∞ Salary: Competitive w/ Warrants\n\nüìç Location: Matrikel1, Central Copenhagen\n\n‚è∞ Deadline: 7th of July 2025','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4251185750/','2025-06-23',NULL,NULL,'[\"Backend-webudvikling\", \"JavaScript\", \"MongoDB\", \"REST APIs\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\", \"Creative Ideation\", \"Databaser\", \"Kode-gennemgang\", \"NoSQL\", \"REST\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:08:01','2025-06-30 14:08:01'),(112,4227318338,'Senior Frontend Developer - Team Sports Applications',61,'H√∏rsholm, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nTeam Sport Application is where Trackman goes beyond golf.\n\nWe build powerful apps and web-based tools that turn raw tracking data into meaningful insights for coaches, analysts, and athletes across professional baseball, softball, American football, and football (soccer).\n\nOur work doesn‚Äôt stop at visualization. The team also plays a key role in collecting and processing data for several key partners‚Äîensuring that our internal tools empower colleagues in the U.S. to efficiently clean, manage, and enrich our datasets. The result? Higher-quality data that delivers even greater value to the athletes and teams who rely on Trackman every day.\n\nWhat we can offer you:\n\nYou will be working with the modern technology together with skilled and‚ÄØpassionate colleagues. You will have the opportunity to take on meaningful responsibilities from the start, with the support and collaboration of the team.\n\nYou will work closely with the other functions of R&D who are all placed under the same roof.‚ÄØ‚ÄØOur solutions are developed by specialists who endlessly explore and challenge new technical boundaries.‚ÄØTrackman has employees from all around the world, and English is our work language.\n\nWhat we are looking for:\n\nYou are an experienced front-end developer, who is enthusiastic about new technologies and cares about clean code. You are curious and excited about software development, and longing to learn and grow with new technologies. You are an independent person, and able to prioritize your responsibilities together with your team. You are a proactively always looking for new challenges and try to improve the code.\n\n \n\nWe expect you to have an educational background in Science or Engineering. Your creative and analytical skills are excellent, and you are structured and well-organized by nature. You juggle several projects at the same time and still keep that critical attention to detail. You take pride in your work.\n\n \n\nResponsibilities:\n\nAs a front-end developer, together with our group of developers, you will be working on various projects. You will be closely working with UI/UX department, Project Managers and Back-end team to plan and refine new features. Therefore, your analytical and critical thinking abilities will be a significant part of the final decision for the new features.\n\n\nCreating visually appealing and responsive web pages \nBuild reusable code and libraries for future use \nOptimizing website performance for speed and efficiency \nKeeping up-to-date with industry trends and best practices \n\n\nRequirements\n\nAt least 5 years of experience\n\n\nThorough understanding of foundational web technologies (HTML, Javascript, CSS), In-depth understanding of the DOM, asynchronous programming, and performance considerations in modern browsers. \nProven track record with modern JavaScript frameworks (e.g., React, Vue) and strong proficiency in TypeScript. \nWork in an agile DevOps environment with a strong focus on collaboration, knowledge sharing, and clear communication. \nComfortable with Node.js for build tooling, hands-on experience with Vite, Webpack, and NPM/Yarn. \nExperience with accessibility standards (Github), CI/CD tools in Azure DevOps. \nExperience with hosting in Azure Portal. \nGood understanding of architectural patterns and software design principals \nSupport consumers of the design system and component library through multiple forms of communication. Actively engage and collaborate with the design community to ensure a consistent and cohesive experience across digital products \n\n\nJoin the home of a powerful sports brand and a one-of-a-kind technology \n\nOur proprietary technology is based on expert knowledge about radar, computer vision, data, and software engineering. Our solutions are developed by specialists who endlessly explore and challenge new technical boundaries. Trackman‚Äôs blend of cutting-edge technology, sports, and continued growth make our company an outstanding place to work.\n\nOur work culture is entrepreneurial, ambitious, and rewarding as you get to collaborate with inspiring colleagues and interact with the leaders of golf, baseball, and football. Based on a unique brand reputation, we are proud to work in close partnership with the top athletes, organizations, and teams that rely on our technology to stay ahead of the race.\n\nWe are a Danish company founded, owned, and managed since 2003 by three entrepreneurs with a strong passion for sports. Today, we have a global footprint with our headquarters located in Denmark (H√∏rsholm) and offices in New York, Phoenix, Seoul and Tokyo. We employ over 800 people worldwide, half of which work in Denmark, where most hardware and software products are developed, tested, and manufactured.\n\nThe Office\n\nWe have just moved to our state-of-art HQ in H√∏rsholm, located at DTU Science Park. We take great pride in the building we designed! The office features bright meeting rooms, coffee areas to catch up with colleagues, a large testing arena with simulators available for employees and a fitness centre, everything surrounded by a beautiful forest and respecting the environment. We made sure to utilize the newest technologies to be energy efficient and be mindful of ventilation and sound propagation.\n\nThe cherry on top is our canteen: with an indoor and outdoor area to enjoy the fresh food prepared by our own kitchen staff.\n\nWhere innovation happens\n\nAt Trackman, we know that great people make great products. We believe that teams thrive, and innovation sparks in an atmosphere where people are encouraged to think for themselves, where everybody‚Äôs voices are heard, and where the best ideas prevail in the pursuit of exceptional solutions. This mix makes Trackman an inspiring company ‚Äì for our customers and colleagues.\n\nShare our Passion!\n\nApplications are continuously assessed, so please send your application as soon as possible. The position is intended for our Trackman Innovation centre in H√∏rsholm, Danish language is not a requirement.\n\nApply now','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4227318338/','2025-06-23',100,NULL,'[\"Brugergr√¶nsefladedesign\", \"CSS\", \"Frontend-udvikling\", \"HTML\", \"JavaScript\", \"React.js\", \"Responsiv webdesign\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"TypeScript\", \"Brugeroplevelse\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:08:01','2025-06-30 14:08:01'),(113,4252067176,'Bliv vores n√¶ste Linux-specialist og bidrag til den gode sags tjeneste i PET',55,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nBr√¶nder du for stabil drift gennem l√∏bende optimering? Har du passion for teknologi og automatisering? Vil du v√¶re en del af det team, som sikrer et robust og tidssvarende Linux-milj√∏? S√• er du m√•ske vores nye kollega.\n\nBliv en del af holdet omkring PET‚Äôs kerneinfrastruktur\n\nSom Linux-specialist hos PET bliver din overordnede opgave at sikre vedligeholdelse og optimering af vores Linux-milj√∏. Du vil f√• en central rolle i etableringen af nye systemer baseret p√• container-teknologi og automatisering, samtidig med at du bliver en del af alle life-cycle faserne for Linux.\n\nAf Konkrete Opgaver Kan N√¶vnes\n\n\n Installere, konfigurere og vedligeholde Linux serverne\n Varetage opdateringer og patch\n Vedligeholde templates og repositories\n Daglig drift og fejls√∏gning\n Automatisere rutineopgaver\n Bidrage til modernisering af systemer og processer\n\n\nDu vil blive en del af PET‚Äôs IT-sektor, som leverer IT-services til hele organisationen. IT-sektoren best√•r af tre centre, et Infrastrukturcenter, et Applikationscenter og et Center for Processer & Support. Du vil blive en del af sektionen for Integrationer, som h√∏rer under vores Center for Infrastruktur. Du vil indg√• i et team af ligesindede Linux-specialister med gode muligheder for faglig sparring, b√•de internt i teamet og uden for teamet med snitflader og samarbejdspartnere i hele PET, hvor Linux anvendes bredt i flere dele af organisationen. Vores kultur er baseret p√• samarbejde, tillid og ansvarlighed. F√¶lles for medarbejderne er √∏nsket om at tjene en meningsfyldt sag, som er st√∏rre end profit og markedsandele.\n\nDu er l√¶renem, proaktiv og har gode samarbejdsevner\n\nFor at f√• succes i stillingen er det vigtigt, at du er nysgerrig p√• ny teknologi og √•ben for nye processer.\n\nStabil, sikker og effektiv drift er fundamentet for vores leverancer, og vi har ladet os inspirere af ITIL til dokumentation af vores processer. Sikkerhed og automatisering bliver t√¶nkt ind i alle dine leverancer, s√• der ikke akkumuleres teknisk g√¶ld. Da automatisering af rutineopgaver vil blive en integreret del af hverdagen, s√• er erfaring med f.eks. Ansible en fordel.\n\nVi ser gerne, at du har en relevant uddannelse inden for IT som f.eks. datamatiker, IT-teknolog, softwareudvikler, IT-ingeni√∏r eller lignende. Din uddannelsesbaggrund er ikke afg√∏rende, s√• l√¶nge du har nogle √•rs erfaring med Linux-systemadministration. Derudover er det en fordel, hvis du tidligere har arbejdet med containers og shell scripting.\n\nI PET v√¶gter vi desuden visse personlige kompetencer h√∏jt. Det er kompetencer, som vi mener, er essentielle for alle PET-ansatte uanset faglig baggrund. Det g√∏r vi, fordi det er vigtigt for os, at vi finder det rette match. Du kan l√¶se om kompetencerne her www.pet.dk/job.\n\nF√• en hverdag, der aldrig bliver hverdag\n\nVores arbejdsplads er som ingen andre. Vores opgave er at forebygge, efterforske og modvirke trusler mod friheden, demokratiet og sikkerheden i det danske samfund. Dette stiller h√∏je krav til vores IT-l√∏sninger, datakvalitet og ikke mindst passionerede og kompetente medarbejdere.\n\nVores kollegaer skal bruge vores arbejde, og vi er med fra start til slut. Mange af os har valgt jobbet for at arbejde med en sag, der er st√∏rre end profit og timefakturering. Vi har et h√∏jere form√•l.\n\nSom Linux-specialist i PET bliver du en del af en hverdag, der er pr√¶get af opgaver, som ikke findes andre steder, og hver dag byder p√• nye udfordringer, som ikke fandtes i g√•r. Vi har en hverdag, der aldrig bliver hverdag, og det kan du ogs√• f√•.\n\nAns√¶ttelsesforhold\n\nAns√¶ttelsesstart pr. 1 november 2025. Grundet sommerferie kan der g√• et stykke tid, f√∏r du h√∏rer fra os. Vi h√•ber meget, at du vil v√¶re t√•lmodig med os. Vi forventer at p√•begynde samtaler i uge 34.\n\nDu kan l√¶se mere om hele PET‚Äôs ans√¶ttelsesproces p√• www.pet.dk/job.\n\nEt ans√¶ttelsesforhold i PET skal behandles med diskretion, hvilket du som ans√∏ger skal v√¶re opm√¶rksom p√•. Det betyder, at du som udgangspunkt godt kan fort√¶lle t√¶tte og fortrolige relationer, som du har tillid til, at du har s√∏gt en stilling i PET, men ikke hvad jobbet indeb√¶rer.\n\nDet er en foruds√¶tning for ans√¶ttelse i PET, at du kan sikkerhedsgodkendes til yderst hemmeligt, ligesom du skal kunne opretholde sikkerhedsgodkendelsen gennem hele din ans√¶ttelse. Som sikkerhedsgodkendt forventes det, at du er s√¶rlig opm√¶rksom p√• din tavshedspligt i forhold til klassificeret information.\n\nHar du en akademisk baggrund, bliver du ansat p√• overenskomstvilk√•r i henhold til de til enhver tid g√¶ldende aftaler mellem Finansministeriet og Akademikernes Centralorganisation. Har du en anden uddannelsesm√¶ssig baggrund, bliver du ansat p√• overenskomstvilk√•r i henhold til den til enhver tid g√¶ldende organisationsaftale for kontorfunktion√¶rer i staten mellem Finansministeriet og HK/STAT samt OAO-S-f√¶llesoverenskomst. Alternativt bliver du ansat p√• anden relevant overenskomst.\n\nDit arbejdssted bliver p√• Klausdalsbrovej 1 i S√∏borg, lige ved siden af Buddinge station, hvor b√•de S-tog og bus k√∏rer lige til d√∏ren. I PET arbejder vi p√• interne systemer og med fortrolige opgaver, og derfor m√∏der vi ogs√• p√• arbejde hver dag for at l√∏se vores opgaver.\n\nYderligere information\n\nDu kan l√¶re meget mere om PET som arbejdsplads p√• www.pet.dk/job, hvor du bl.a. kan l√¶se mere om alle de fagligheder, der arbejder i PET og deres hverdag. Du kan ogs√• lytte til vores podcastserie ‚ÄôTjenesten og truslerne‚Äô.\n\nDu er ogs√• altid meget velkommen til at kontakte os p√• hverdage p√• mail hr-rekruttering@politi.dk eller p√• telefon +45 24 62 18 45, hvis du har sp√∏rgsm√•l til stillingen, PET som arbejdsplads eller lignende.\n\nN√•r du s√∏ger en stilling hos PET, giver du lov til, at vi m√• indhente dit CPR-nummer via CPR-registeret med henblik p√• identifikation af dig i forbindelse med rekrutteringsprocessen. Vi indhenter dit CPR-nummer, s√• vi sikkert kan fremsende relevante og n√∏dvendige dokumenter til dig via Digital Post.\n\nDet er vigtigt for os, at PET afspejler den mangfoldighed, som vi arbejder for. Derfor opfordrer vi alle interesserede, uanset k√∏n, alder, religion, seksualitet og etniske tilh√∏rsforhold til at s√∏ge stillingen.\n\nTr√¶d ind i en lukket verden, der √•bner nye d√∏re, hvor vi udvikler os, tr√¶ner og bygger videre p√• det, vi kan. Om vi udvikler nye systemer, analyserer data eller finjusterer fodstillingen til skydetr√¶ning, s√• er vi altid p√• t√¶erne. Det skaber gode muligheder for, at du kan rykke dig med os, vokse med opgaverne og √•bne nye d√∏re i dit arbejdsliv.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4252067176/','2025-06-23',NULL,NULL,'[\"Ansible\", \"Bash\", \"Linux\", \"Linux-systemadministration\", \"Styresystemer\", \"Unix\", \"RHEL\", \"Red Hat Linux\", \"Script\", \"Systemadministration\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:08:01','2025-06-30 14:08:01'),(114,4259433481,'Validation Lead for Global Contract Manufacturing Devices',2,'Hiller√∏d, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nAre you a detail-oriented professional with expertise in medical device validation? Are you able to navigate critical validation processes on new production lines, and lead validation strategy? If so, we want to hear from you!\n\nJoin us at Hiller√∏d as our next Validation Lead at Global Contract Manufacturing Devices (GCMD) ‚Äì apply now!\n\nThe position\n\nAs a Validation Lead, you will be the validation expert for the team, responsible for leading the alignment and implementation of Validation Strategies within the department. In this role, you will be responsible for planning, executing, and reporting on validation activities for medical devices. Your role will involve direct engagement with Contract Manufacturing Organizations (CMOs) to effectively translate