and drive and contribute to new initiatives that can take our software development processes to new and greater heights.\n\nAdditionally, you will‚Ä¶\n\n\nOwn your tasks from beginning to end, including partaking in the design of the solution with our UX team and product owners‚Äì because who knows, maybe your idea is better? We‚Äôd like to know! \nAssist in improving our architecture and the reduction of technical debt \nDrive and contribute to new initiatives such as IaC, DevOps, CI/CD \nBring new ideas to the table to help us improve ‚Äì either through code, processes or something entirely different! \n\n\nOur tech \n\nBuilt on a distributed cloud system featuring AWS and ElasticSearch, our main codebase consists of C#, Angular and TypeScript.\n\nWe aim to offer our customers and users new features and an improved product continuously, and in order to meet this goal, the development is characterized by agile methodologies and loosely defined time estimates, with approximately six annual releases.\n\nYour background \n\nWe believe you...\n\n\nHave strong experience with C# and .NET. \nAre also capable and willing to handle frontend tickets, as we\'re a fullstack team with full ownership of the features we\'re delivering \nHave a solid theoretical foundation from a degree in computer science, engineering, IT or similar. \nValue security, maintainability and reliability in delivered work. \nAre proactive, solution-oriented and able to work both independently and as part of a team. \n\n\nBut most important is your ambitious attitude towards your continuous learning and development, and the wish to actively participate in the development of our products.\n\nWhat To Expect As a Daluxian\n\nOur flat organization, where the way from idea to product is short combined with creative freedom and a high level of trust in your work, ensures that you will be able to create tangible value for our users.\n\nYou will become a part of a highly skilled team of passionate and young individuals driven by the wish to explore new and reshape existing technologies. Everyday life is characterized by sparring between colleagues, room to be yourself, with monthly social events and various clubs to mix professional development with fun.\n\nAs Dalux is a software company, we want half of the company to consist of Software Developers. All our software development happens at our head office at Vibenshuset in Copenhagen.\n\nReady for the next step \n\nIf the description above and Dalux sounds like a place where you could develop and contribute to the high-quality software, we would gladly accept your CV. We will be having ongoing interviews.\n\nIf you have any questions feel free to contact IT Talent Acquisition Specialist, David Steen Christensen, dst@dalux.com.\n\nWho Is Dalux\n\nDalux is a Danish software company founded in 2005 by Ph.D. Bent Dalgaard and Torben Dalgaard. Dalux‚Äô products are aimed at making the construction industry smarter and more effective. Our user-friendly digital tools and Building Information Modelling-technology (also known as BIM) is used in more than 140 countries globally.\n\nWe are crazy about cool technology and have experience being first movers on new tech. Our products are based on our unique 3D BIM-technology and makes use of AR - all developed entirely by Dalux.\n\nApplication deadline:\n\nOngoing','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4223910229/','2025-06-23',71,NULL,'[\".NET\", \"Angular\", \"Backend-webudvikling\", \"C\", \"C#\", \"Datalogi\", \"OOP\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\", \"XML\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:09:33','2025-06-30 14:09:33'),(125,4209799866,'Software Developer in Test - Golf Mobile Applications',61,'H√∏rsholm, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nAre you a talented and driven‚ÄØQuality Assurance Engineer with an interest in testing‚ÄØsports products?\n\n \n\nTrackman is the leading brand in its field and acknowledged by athletes all over the world. We are experiencing high growth and looking for‚ÄØa‚ÄØtalented‚ÄØquality assurance engineer with passion for automation‚ÄØto help make our products even better.\n\nThis position offers you a unique opportunity to work with the development of a product composed of various hardware and software platforms. This means that you will get a lot of opportunities through your work life at Trackman to learn new skills. Your input and way of challenging existing working routines will be appreciated, and you get to work with a cool, market-leading brand!\n\nYou will become part of a cross-functional team of skilled developers, QA‚Äôs, UI/UX, product owners, etc. and you will have the chance to impact your own way of working. Our company culture is open, informal, and fun ‚Äì and we continuously aim to heighten our quality as well as the individuals‚Äô capabilities and skills.\n\nYou will be part of the Trackman Golf Mobile‚ÄØteam.‚ÄØYour key task is to help Trackman make the right products in high quality through design, maintenance, and execution of test scripts, test cases, scenarios and more. The task is heavier on the test automation side but does require manual testing skills as well.\n\nCore Responsibilities:\n\nAs our new quality assurance and automation engineer, you will:\n\n\nWork closely with the stakeholders to deliver high quality for our products. \nContribute with the QA team to design, maintain and run test cases. \nAutomate UI Tests for our Android and iOS apps using Appium C#. \n\n\nRequirements\n\n The ideal candidate must have:\n\n\nA relevant education in Computer Science or equivalent (minimum bachelor level)\n5+ years‚ÄØof experience‚ÄØin the‚ÄØQA field, test plans and designing test cases\nExperience with testing mobile apps\nExperience with Appium with C# or Java\nExperience with test case management tools (Preferably Azure DevOps Test Plans)\nGood communications skills\nAttention to details\n\n\nIt will also be a plus if you have:\n\n\nGolf knowledge (You don\'t need to be a pro golfer; it can be simply a hobby)\nExperience with Unit Testing tools like MSTest, XUnit, NUnit\n\n\n We offer:\n\n\nWorking with and testing the leading tracking brand in its field\nHighly skilled colleagues\nInternational environment with more than 35 nationalities in our HQ\nSocial activities\n\n\n \n\nThe Office\n\nA state-of-art HQ in H√∏rsholm, located at DTU Science Park. We take great pride of the building we designed! The office features bright meeting rooms, coffee areas to catch up with colleagues, a large testing arena with simulators available for employees and a fitness centre, everything surrounded by a beautiful forest and respecting the environment. We made sure to utilize the newest technologies to be energy efficient and be mindful of ventilation and sound propagation.\n\nThe cherry on top is our canteen: with indoor and outdoor area to enjoy the fresh food prepared by our own kitchen staff.\n\nJoin the home of a powerful sports brand and a one-of-a-kind technology\n\nOur proprietary technology is based on expert knowledge about radar, computer vision, data, and software engineering. Our solutions are developed by specialists who endlessly explore and challenge new technical boundaries. Trackman‚Äôs blend of cutting-edge technology, sports, and continued growth make our company an outstanding place to work. Our work culture is entrepreneurial, ambitious, and rewarding as you get to collaborate with inspiring colleagues and interact with the leaders of golf, baseball, and football. Based on a unique brand reputation, we are proud of working in close partnership with the top athletes, organizations, and teams that rely on our technology to stay ahead of the race.\n\nWe are a Danish company founded, owned, and managed since 2003 by three entrepreneurs with a strong passion for sports. Today, we have a global footprint with our headquarter located in Denmark (H√∏rsholm) and offices in New York, Phoenix, Poland, Seoul‚ÄØand Tokyo. We employ more than 700 worldwide, half of which work in Denmark, where most hardware and software products are developed, tested and manufactured.\n\nWhere innovation happens\n\nAt Trackman, we know that great people make great products. We believe that teams thrive and innovation sparks in an atmosphere where people are encouraged to think for themselves, where everybody‚Äôs voices are heard, and where the best ideas prevail in the pursuit of the exceptional solution. This mix is what makes Trackman an inspiring company ‚Äì for our customers and our colleagues.\n\nInterested?\n\nApplications are continuously assessed, so please send your application.\n\n \n\nShare our Passion!\n\nThe position is intended for our H√∏rsholm HQ, Danish language is not a requirement.\n\nIf you have what it takes, apply today and join a company with great technologies, passionate colleagues, and great opportunities to grow.\n\nApply now','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4209799866/','2025-06-23',59,NULL,'[\"C#\", \"Datalogi\", \"JIRA\", \"Java\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Testarbejde med software\", \"Kvalitetssikring\", \"Testautomatisering\", \"Testeksempler\", \"Testplanl√¶gning\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:09:33','2025-06-30 14:09:33'),(126,4248471434,'Senior Software Engineer - Backend (Parcels)',62,'K√∏benhavns Kommune, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nAt Too Good To Go, we have an ambitious goal: to inspire and empower everyone to fight food waste together.\n\n40% of all food produced in the world is wasted. And that has a huge impact on the health of our planet, with 10% of greenhouse gas emissions coming from food waste.\n\nWe‚Äôre more than an app: we are a certified B Corporation with a mission to empower everyone to take action against food waste, so alongside our marketplace app, we create educational tools, explore new business solutions - such as our Retail Technologies offering, and influence legislation to help reduce food waste.\n\nWe‚Äôre growing fast: Our community of 120 million registered users and 247,000 active partners across 19 countries, have together already prevented 453+ million meals from going to waste - avoiding over 1.224.000 tonnes of CO2e!\n\nThe Role\n\nWe are looking for a Senior Backend Engineer, to be a part of our Manufacturing Teams that define, build and deliver our product features. As a Team Member in a product team, you will work towards specific outcomes with the freedom and responsibility to figure out the best way to achieve them together with the other Engineers and other Product Team members.\n\nYou‚Äôll be joining the Parcels (Manufacturing) team, a fast-growing and relatively new part of the Too Good To Go. This team is behind the Delivery tab in the app, which enables users to purchase parcels and have them delivered directly to their homes.\n\nThe Parcels product is already live in several countries, including Denmark, Germany, and Italy, with more launches on the horizon. As part of this expanding business area, you‚Äôll have the opportunity to help shape and build exciting new features while contributing to a product that‚Äôs scaling rapidly across markets.\n\nYour mission will be to help refine, design, implement, deliver and maintain various product features.\n\nThe Tech Stack\n\nWe have created a scalable Spring Boot Application running on Java 21 in Kubernetes, deployed in a multi-region setup in AWS. Developers are able to run a full development environment locally, which gives a great developer experience.\n\nResponsibilities\n\n\nBuild and evolve our backend services and infrastructure to stay ahead of our growth curve.\nDevelop exciting new features for our customers and businesses who partner with us.\nActively participate in your team‚Äôs agile development processes with a continuous improvement mindset.\nStrive to deliver international top-class products with maximum quality, maintainability and scalability.\nTake on additional tasks outside your current boundaries with help from your team to continue to grow and expand your skills.\n\n\nThe ideal candidate\n\n\nYou have a proactive, ownership-driven mindset, and thrive in fast-paced start-up like teams\nA wealth of experience in Backend development with the Java ecosystem.\nProven production experience with Java, SpringBoot, MySQL, Message System & GIT.\nHas worked with Domain Driven Design, and Clean, or Hexagonal Architecture.\nKnowledge of AWS services (SQS, SNS, S3‚Ä¶), ElasticSearch, Redis, Docker, Kubernetes.\nExperience with Restful APIs.\nExperience with building scalable solutions.\nEnjoys actively participating in a cross-functional product team.\nTakes pride in writing quality code.\n\n\nOur values\n\n\nWe win together: Food waste is a big beast to fight. We believe in a #oneteam.\nWe raise the bar: We always push for more. We work smart, smash barriers and elevate one another.\nWe keep it simple: Our ambitions are bold but our solutions are simple.\nWe build a legacy: We‚Äôre proud of the change we‚Äôre driving. \nWe care: We always look out for each other. Caring is also about the way we do business. We do the right thing.\n\n\nWhat We Have To Offer\n\n\nAn opportunity to work in a global social-impact company and certified B Corporation! where you can see a real and tangible impact in your role.\nTo be an integral member of our defined product teams. We are eager for you to make an impact and contribute to the product scope and development; Your insights are valuable, and we are here to listen.\nWork-life balance is important to us! Focus on the job to be done, not the hours spent, there is no need for overtime. On-call duty is not part of the job, but can be additionally agreed upon should you and your manager both wish it. We believe that happy environments create happy employees. \nWe trust in our employees and encourage an autonomous environment that provides several opportunities for employees to contribute, develop and take ownership of their work in a way that works for them.\nTo be part of an international company, with over 1,300+ colleagues across 19 countries that are on the same important mission.\nAn informal environment, working alongside 180+ passionate people within Tech & Product\nWe celebrate our differences and our successes and have a strong values-driven team culture.\nWe work in a hybrid set-up and value in office work weekly.\nWe may be able to support you with a working visa in Copenhagen, please be prepared to discuss this topic further as your first stage interview.\n\n\nHow To Apply\n\n\nWe take recruitment very seriously, so please carefully read everything we have written above.\nPlease also check our website and international media in order to get a good overview of Too Good To Go.\nPlease submit your CV and Cover letter in English.\nPlease note that we only accept applications coming through our platform. No CV or Cover Letter will be accepted by email or LinkedIn direct messaging.\n\n\nJob Ref\n\nA Movement for Everyone\n\nWe want to inspire and empower everyone to fight food waste together. With that mission, it‚Äôs only natural that we want to build a diverse and inclusive team of highly capable individuals who are passionate about doing things in a better way. We strongly believe we all excel and are more creative when we‚Äôre allowed to be ourselves, and we‚Äôre committed to a culture where all of us belong.\n\nWe are an equal opportunity employer and all employment is decided on the basis of qualifications, merit and business need. If you need reasonable accommodation at any point in the application or interview process, please let us know.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4248471434/','2025-06-16',35,NULL,'[\"Backend-webudvikling\", \"Java\", \"JavaScript\", \"Kubernetes\", \"OOP\", \"REST APIs\", \"SQL\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\", \"REST\", \"XML\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:09:33','2025-06-30 14:09:33'),(127,4248176238,'Technology Analyst (Cloud Technology)',64,'K√∏benhavns Kommune, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nNORTH is looking for talented students with technical backgrounds who aspire towards a career in consulting. As a Technology Analyst, you will get the chance to work directly with our clients on diverse technology projects with a focus on sales and service operations.\n\n\n\n\nYour responsibilities\n\nAs a Technology Analyst, you will support our global clients with commercial transformation from design to implementation. Together with your team, you will engage in projects, where you will act as a trusted advisor in shaping best-practices solutions to solve business challenges in sales and service operations. You will typically be involved in all project phases identifying best-practice technical solutions in standard systems such as Salesforce. You must be passionate about the following areas:\n\n\n\n\nCutting-edge cloud-based technologies\nAdvising on everything between platform selection, integration, and software architecture\nAchieving tangible business results leveraging the newest technology\n\n\n\n\nYour skills and experience\n\nTo succeed in the role, you have strong technical, analytical, and problem-solving skills. Preferably, you have knowledge or experience with solution design and sales and service processes. As a person, you like to have a responsibility, where you continuously seek to improve the quality of your work. You are curious, learn to dare, and are comfortable in teams with an empathic mindset. You have the following skills and experience:\n\n\n\n\nYou are studying a bachelor‚Äôs or master‚Äôs degree within engineering or technology\nYou have experience in programming in an object-oriented language\nYou are knowledgeable about relational databases\nYou have great communication skills and are fluent in written and spoken English\nYou have an interest in working in the field between technology and business\nYou want to become part of the consulting industry\n\n\n\n\nWe expect that you are flexible and co-operative, and that you can work independently under changing conditions. You should be able to work 2-3 days a week, however, we also understand that you must attend to and prioritise your studies, and we are aware that there will be times when assignments and exams occupy you. Furthermore, it will be possible to work full-time for a short or long period of time for example in between semesters.\n\n\n\n\nWhat we offer you\n\nWe offer a challenging, dynamic, and welcoming environment, where you will get the opportunity to work with global transformation projects. You will get excellent development opportunities among highly competent and ambitious colleagues and leaders as well as regular mentoring and feedback to support your rapid development. You will work with a high degree of freedom and extensive responsibility while getting support from your team in an effort to become better at helping our clients create exceptional results continually.\n\nYou will get a unique opportunity to influence projects and your position in a rapidly developing environment. Last but not least, you will join a culture with a family vibe, a down-to-earth spirit, and a social gathering agenda.\n\n\n\n\nHow you apply\n\nPlease send your motivational letter, university transcripts from your bachelor\'s and master\'s degrees, and CV via the link. We process applications and arrange interviews continually. The start date is flexible, but the sooner, the better.\n\n\n\n\nTo apply for this role, you must hold a valid work permit that allows for employment in Denmark and permits international travel on par with EU/EFTA citizenship rights.\n\n\n\n\nPlease don\'t hesitate to reach out by e-mail to recruiting@north.consulting, if you have any questions.\n\n\n\n\nWe look forward to receiving your application!','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4248176238/','2025-06-16',40,NULL,'[\"Datalogi\", \"Analytiske kompetencer\", \"CRM\", \"Datamodellering\", \"L√∏sningsarkitektur\", \"Process engineering\", \"Systemkonfiguration\", \"Technical Solution Design\"]',NULL,'2025-06-30 14:09:33','2025-06-30 14:09:33'),(128,4259433458,'Experienced Automation Engineers Pipeline for Hiller√∏d',2,'Hiller√∏d, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nAre you ready to take the next step and pursue a life-changing career at Novo Nordisk? Are you driven by automation and digitalization of the Novo Nordisk manufacturing value chain? Look no further!\n\nWe are building a talent pipeline for skilled and innovative automation engineers to join Novo Nordisk in shaping the future through automation.\n\nJoining the Automation Engineers Pipeline\nBy applying for the pipeline, you will be considered as a potential match for on-site automation related positions, which align with your background, skills, and interests across various areas in Denmark.\n\nWe‚Äôll match your profile proactively with relevant positions. Once a Hiring Manager shows interest in your profile, the Hiring Manager Team will reach out to you and tell you more about the current position and invite you for the 1st Interview.\n\nLocations\nWe are looking for candidates to all our locations. This specific pipeline covers on-site positions in Hiller√∏d.\n\nWe look forward to receiving your application and to having the opportunity to provide a solid match for open positions.\n\nAbout The Positions\n\nDue to the expansion of our activities in all business areas and sites, we are currently seeking talents for many different teams across Novo Nordisk, such as Advanced automation, Manufacturing Execution Systems (MES), and Collaborative- and industrial robotics. We encourage you to read more detailed information about the different roles and areas through this link: Automation engineers and process digitalization (novonordisk.com)\n\nQualifications\n\nWe are looking for someone with an innovative and solution-oriented mindset. As you will be working and collaborating with people from various departments in the organization, it would be 