ation and cross-functional collaboration\nProject coordination or agile delivery experience\nFluent in English with effective verbal and written communication skills\n\n\nCompetencies\n\nAs a person you:\n\n\nHave an interest in exploring business processes and practices for a deeper understanding of how systems function in the organizational context and experience designing user journeys\nAre professional and committed by nature with a solid sense of quality, and include focus on continuous service improvement and optimizations in all you do\nAre flexible with a can-do attitude and an innovative mindset, and you thrive in an exciting environment with progressive people\nAre self-motivated - you can act on your own. If you see issues while implementing a solution, you make sure that this is noted to be included in future prioritizations\nAre familiar with agile ways of working and contribute actively in a collaborative development setting\nValue simplicity and clarity in your solutions, aiming to reduce complexity and deliver intuitive user experiences\nAppreciate building relationships and working closely with others to create shared understanding and alignment\n\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nWork in a dynamic and innovative environment, where you will have the opportunity to shape the future of digital collaboration and workplace solutions at Vestas. Opportunities for professional growth and development, with access to training and development programs.\n\nBe part of a collaborative culture that values teamwork and knowledge sharing and work according to the Vestas values; Simplicity, Collaboration, Accountability and Passion.\n\nAdditional Information\n\nThe position may be based at our offices in Aarhus or Copenhagen (Denmark), Warsaw or Szczecin (Poland), Hamburg (Germany), Porto (Portugal), Manila (Philippines) or Chennai (India). Please note that relocation support is not provided for this position. We therefore encourage applicants who are already based near one of th