ices meet the highest standards of excellence.\nSoftware Development: Design, implement, test, troubleshoot, and debug software, actively participating in test strategy definition and implementation alongside your colleagues.\n\n\nWe‚Äôre Looking For a Teammate With\n\n\nEducated in Computer Science, Software Engineering or with a scientific background.\nHave a working experience of at least 3 years in software development.\nFamiliar with software languages like Go, JavaScript/node.js or you can pick it up fast.\nFamiliar with microservice architecture and development with clean, tested code and well-documented.\nDeep knowledge of established design patterns.\nCloud infrastructure: Docker container engines, Kubernetes, and related tools like Grafana, Splunk/Dynatrace.\n\n\nThe location for this role is:\n\n\nLund, Sweden.\nFlexible working conditions and the possibility of working sometimes from home upon agreement.\n\n\nJoin us and take on a role where you can contribute to the success of our team and make a tangible impact on the future of our company. If you‚Äôre passionate about learning, solving new problems, and building awesome software, we want to hear from you.\n\nMore About Qlik And Who We Are\n\nFind out more about life at Qlik on social: Instagram, LinkedIn, YouTube, and X/Twitter, and to see all other opportunities to join us and our values, check out our Careers Page.\n\nWhat else do we offer?\n\n\nGenuine career progression pathways and mentoring programs\nCulture of innovation, technology, collaboration, and openness\nFlexible, diverse, and international work environment\n\n\nGiving back is a huge part of our culture. Alongside an extra ‚Äúchange the world‚Äù day plus another for personal development, we also highly encourage participation in our Corporate Responsibility Employee Programs\n\nIf you need assistance applying for a role due to a disability, please submit your request via [email protected]. Any information you provide will be treated according to Qlik‚Äôs Recruitment Privacy Notice. Qlik may only respond to emails related to accommodation requests.\n\nQlik is not accepting unsolicited assistance from search firms for this employment opportunity. Please, no phone calls or emails. All resumes submitted by search firms to any employee at Qlik via-email, the Internet or in any form and/or method without a valid written search agreement in place for this position will be deemed the sole property of Qlik. No fee will be paid in the event the candidate is hired by Qlik as a result of the referral or through other means.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4259607132/','2025-07-01',6,NULL,'[\"Backend-webudvikling\", \"Datalogi\", \"JavaScript\", \"Kubernetes\", \"Microservices\", \"OOP\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Webtjenester Amazon (AWS)\", \"Kreativ probleml√∏sning\", \"XML\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 09:53:05','2025-07-01 09:53:05'),(243,4256496382,'Digital B2B Systems & Business Analyst',130,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\n\n\nDigital B2B Systems & Business Analyst\n\nSeize the opportunity to help transform the digital landscape at Carlsberg Group. As the Business Analyst in the Digital Growth & Execution team, you will help us drive impactful innovation on how Carlsberg sells and engage with our B2B customers, ensuring scalability and harmonization of our customer-facing digital solutions.\n\nIn this role, you will be collaborating closely with product managers, local markets, Carlsberg IIT teams, and external partners. If you‚Äôre interested in enabling digital connectivity and commercial execution across markets to create great customer experiences, this role is for you.\n\nWhat You‚Äôll Be Doing\n\nYour main tasks will be analyzing business processes and data to identify opportunities to streamline and to improve the impact of our commercial technologies. This could be through process standardization, framing of new customer-facing features, testing different innovative solutions,