platforme. Du kender til kommunikationsv√¶rkt√∏jer som sociale medier, nyhedsbreve og kampagneplatforme, og har muligvis erfaring med m√•lrettet annoncering.\n\n\n\n\nDu har forretningsforst√•else og kan gennemskue v√¶rdik√¶der. Erfaring fra transport, logistik, affald eller energi er et plus, men vigtigst er det, at du interesserer dig for milj√∏ og cirkul√¶r √∏konomi.\n\n\n\n\nDet forventer vi:\n\nAt du er iderig og har evnen til at konceptualisere dine id√©er, s√• de kan eksekveres i nye formater og relevant kommunikation.\n\n\n\n\nDu har fokus p√• at levere og er dygtig til at f√• produceret og distribueret indhold og budskaber. Du er hurtig til at oms√¶tte planer til praksis.\n\n\n\n\nDu er tillidsskabende, nysgerrig og lydh√∏r og har mod p√• at have kontakt med mange forskellige medarbejdertyper i en kompleks milj√∏virksomhed og kan vinde tillid.\n\n\n\n\nDet kan du forvente af os:\n\nI Dansk Retursystem er vi alle med til at g√∏re en forskel for klima og milj√∏. Vi henter og sorterer tomme flasker og d√•ser med pant og s√∏rger for, at de bliver genanvendt til nye. Og vi arbejder hver dag p√• at mindske vores CO2-aftryk.\n\n\n\n\nVi er en virksomhed med fokus p√• et trygt og sikkert arbejdsmilj√∏, hvor du altid kan f√• hj√¶lp af dine kollegaer. Vi har respekt for hinanden, og vi vil gerne have det sjovt.\n\n\n\n\nVi har en st√¶rk og mangfoldig kultur. Vores medarbejdere er vant til at tage ansvar og finde l√∏sninger, s√• du f√•r b√•de indflydelse og frihed i jobbet. Samtidig er der plads til forskellighed. I 2024 vandt vi en pris som Danmarks 6. bedste arbejdsplads ved Great Place To Work, s√• vi g√∏r, hvad vi siger.\n\n\n\n\nAns√∏gning \n\nLyder jobbet som noget for dig s√• send os straks dit cv og ans√∏gning. Ans√∏gningsfristen er 10. august 2025, og vi forventer at afholde samtaler i uge 33 og 34. \n\n\n\n\nHar du sp√∏rgsm√•l, er du velkommen til at kontakte Mikkel Brandrup, Chef for Kommunikation & Public Affairs p√• mbra@dansk-retursystem.dk eller 28899912 (kun i uge 31-32). Forvent forl√¶nget svartid p√• mail pga. sommerferie.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4256461362/','2025-06-30',17,NULL,'[\"Business process improvement\", \"Driftsledelse\", \"Forretningsadministration\", \"IT-serviceadministration\", \"Kommunikation\", \"Procesforbedring\", \"Procesoptimering\", \"Public affairs\", \"Salgspr√¶sentationer\", \"Six Sigma\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:23:03','2025-07-01 10:23:03'),(409,4252510734,'Computer graphics developer',51,'K√∏benhavns Kommune, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nAre you passionate about advanced graphics and software development? With us, you‚Äôll get the chance to work with cutting-edge technologies like DirectX 11/12 (e.g., Direct3D) in a cloud-based setup ‚Äì and leave your mark on everything from architecture to new features. Step into a role where your ideas aren‚Äôt just heard ‚Äì they become part of the product.\n\nYour new role\n\nAs an experienced computer graphics developer, we expect you will take responsibility for implementing tasks of medium to high complexity, actively contributing to our software architecture and cross-team collaborations. Depending on your experiences and interests, you will build new features for our existing platform, and drive and contribute to new initiatives that can take our software development processes to new and greater heights.\n\nAdditionally, you will‚Ä¶\n\n\n Own your tasks from beginning to end, including partaking in the design of the solution with our Product design team and Product managers ‚Äì because who knows, maybe your idea is better? We‚Äôd like to know! \n Assist in improving our architecture and the reduction of technical debt \n Bring new ideas to the table to help us improve ‚Äì either through code, processes or something entirely different! \n\n\nOur tech\n\nBuilt on a distributed cloud system, our computer graphics software consists of C# and DirectX 11/12.\n\nWe aim offer our customers and users new features and an improved product continuously, and in order to meet this goal, the development is characterized by agile methodologies and loosely defined time estimates, with approximately six annual releases.\n\nYour background\n\nWe believe you...\n\n\n Have strong experience in Software Development (experience with C# and DirectX) \n Have a solid theoretical foundation from a bachelor‚Äôs degree in computer science, engineering, IT or similar. \n Value security, maintainability and reliability in delivered work. \n Are proactive, solution-oriented and able to work both independently and as part of a team. \n\n\nBut most important is your ambitious attitude towards your continuous learning and development, and the wish to actively participate in the development of our products.\n\nWhat To Expect As a Daluxian\n\nAt Dalux, we foster a creative, collaborative, and supportive environment where your ideas make an impact. Here‚Äôs what you can look forward to as part of our team:\n\n\n Central location in Copenhagen, focus on work/life balance without any overtime, and no dress code. \n An active social environment with monthly events and social clubs. \n Flat communication in our organization, where the journey from idea to product is short combined with creative freedom and a high level of trust in your work, ensures that you will be able to create tangible value for our users. \n You will join a highly specialized, international team with room for creativity and professional growth. \n Strong focus on diversity and inclusion ‚Äì your ideas are heard, and opportunities are available to all. \n Attractive employee benefits such as health insurance, lunch plan, coffee and fruit, free fitness facilities, and free parking garage. \n Focus on your development and well-being, with support for both professional goals and personal growth. \n\n\nReady for the next step\n\nIf Dalux sounds like a place where you could develop and contribute to the high-quality software, we would gladly accept your application. We will be having ongoing interviews.\n\nIf you have any questions, feel free to contact IT TAS, Simone Jena Berg Christensen sch@dalux.com\n\nWho Is Dalux\n\nDalux is a Danish software company founded in 2005 by Ph.D. Bent Dalgaard and Torben Dalgaard. Dalux‚Äô products are aimed at making the construction industry smarter and more effective. Our user-friendly digital tools and Building Information Modelling-technology (also known as BIM) is used in more than 140 countries globally.\n\nWe are crazy about cool technology and have experience being first movers on new tech. Our products are based on our unique 3D BIM-technology and makes use of AR - all developed entirely by Dalux.\n\nApplication deadline:\n\nAs soon as possible','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4252510734/','2025-06-30',13,NULL,'[\"Backend-webudvikling\", \"C\", \"C#\", \"Datalogi\", \"Git\", \"JavaScript\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Computergrafik\", \"Grafik\", \"XML\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:23:06','2025-07-01 10:23:06'),(410,4259406451,'Applikationssupporter',185,'K√∏benhavn og omegn','Om jobbet\n\nHar du et skarpt √∏je for fejlfinding og en serviceorienteret tilgang? Motiveres du af at hj√¶lpe brugere med tekniske udfordringer? S√• er du m√•ske vores nye Applikationssupporter!\n\n\n\n\nOm stillingen:\n\nHos Edora s√∏ger vi en engageret og teknisk dygtig Applikationssupporter til at styrke vores supportteam. I denne rolle vil du spille en central rolle i at sikre en professionel og effektiv kundeoplevelse samt h√•ndtere tekniske udfordringer for brugere af WorkforcePlanner (WFP) og Leverand√∏rPlatformen (LP).\n\n\n\n\nWorkforcePlanner (WFP) er et ressourcestyringsv√¶rkt√∏j, der anvendes af jobcentre, borgerservice, sundhedssektoren og fritidsforvaltninger til at automatisere planl√¶gningsopgaver og borgerbookinger. Leverand√∏rPlatformen (LP) underst√∏tter ordrer, afrapportering og faktureringsstyring i forbindelse med borgerforl√∏b hos kommunernes partnere.\n\n\n\n\nSom Applikation