r.\n\nF√∏lg med her, hvor Regash og Camilla fort√¶ller om jobbet i f√∏tex! \n\nNu Skal Det Handle Om Dig ‚Äì For Du\n\n\nhar god energi og personlighed som s√¶tter et positivt pr√¶g p√• arbejdet og dine kollegaer\nviser stabilitet og ansvarlighed idet du m√∏der op til dine aftalte vagter og tager ansvar n√•r du er p√• arbejde\ner under 18 √•r\n\n\nEr du klar til at sende din ans√∏gning afsted?\n\nHvis du stadig er nysgerrig p√• de mange muligheder f√∏tex kan tilbyde, og er klar til at give den fuld gas i f√∏tex‚Äô bl√• uniform, s√• klik p√• linket nedenfor og lad os h√∏re mere om, hvem du er. Vi gl√¶der os meget til at h√∏re fra dig :)\n\nSalling Group er en mangfoldig arbejdsplads med 60.000 medarbejdere i Danmark, Tyskland og Polen.\n\nVi driver butikker, varehuse, cafeer, spisesteder og webshops med v√¶gt p√• kvalitet, service og omtanke for de samfund og den klode, vi er en del af.\n\nVi br√¶nder for at g√∏re hverdagen bedre for vores kunder','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4260009628/','2025-07-01',NULL,NULL,'[\"Coaching\", \"Elektronik\", \"Finans\", \"Kundeservice\", \"Kundetilfredshed\", \"Loan Workouts\", \"Samarbejdsevner\", \"Sociale medier\", \"Superviseringskompetencer\", \"Teamlederskab\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:23:39','2025-07-01 10:23:39'),(418,4256437961,'Head of Hydraulic System Development',189,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nDepartment Manager within Hydraulics and Injection Development\n\nDo you aspire to join Everllence, a distinguished leader in the maritime industry, dedicated to making a difference with sustainable solutions for the worlds shipping industry. We are the leading designer of two-stroke engines for the propulsion of large ocean-going merchant vessels, and our technology contributes significantly to the decarbonisation of the shipping industry. Our goal is to provide technology with the highest energy efficiency and to enable global shipping to run on carbon-neutral fuels derived from renewable energy sources, such as methanol and ammonia.\n\nAll fuel injection and valve actuation on our engines is driven by extremely fast and powerful hydraulic systems, and new engine designs usually require development of new hydraulic and fuel injection components and systems.\n\nIf you thrive in a fast paced technology development environment and share our passion for decarbonizing the shipping industry, the position as Head of the newly formed department Hydraulic System Development at Everllence R&D in Copenhagen could be the perfect fit for you.\n\nYou will play an responsible role in: \n\n\nManaging a group of approx. 10 highly skilled experts. Initially an important part will be to set the team by additional recruitments.\nLeading the ideation process, concept development, and prototype design for on-engine and off-engine hydraulic systems and leading the preparation of design manuals/guidelines, according to which final design of components and systems for on-engine and off-engine hydraulics is made\nCo-operation with a wide variety of internal and external stakeholders, e.g. engineering departments, procurement, suppliers, engine builders to ensure that the developed concepts are delivering the right technical solutions in a modularized and simple way at the lowest possible cost.\nEnsuring that every member of the team thrives and develops professionally\nShare knowledge and experience and hereby contribute significantly to the success of the development of new components and systems.\n\n\nWe imagine that you\n\n\nHave a M.Sc. in Engineering within professional experience from the shipping or industrial sector and related to engine technology, hydraulics or mechatronic systems, or process system technology.\nHave leadership experience with leading projects and people. Experience in R&D is an advantage.\nHave international experience, ideally involving collaboration with partners in China, South Korea, and/or Japan.\nAre good at building up and maintaining good and trustful professional relationships with many and diverse stakeholders\nSee the value in developing people and organization\nAre a team player and good at both understanding the relevance of a task or problem in the context of an organization and the final product.\n\n\nWelcome to the Hydraulics and Injection Development Department\n\nYou will join the management team of the function area Hydraulics and Injection Development of two-stroke R&D. We are responsible of developing fuel injection/admission concepts and concepts for hydraulic actuation for other on-engine and off-engine mechatronic systems. We analyze structural and thermal loads on our components, run transient simulations of complex hydraulic systems and model with CFD fuel injection, combustion and emission formation. Finally we have a testing department responsible for conducting tests of both experimental and final design on both hydraulic test rigs and engines on either test bed or service.\n\nThe working atmosphere is relaxed, and everyone is committed to succeeding as a team by being supportive and flexible. There is space for creativity and to play with new ideas.\n\nUnleash your potential: Join us towards a carbon-neutral future\n\nAt Everllence, we offer you the chance to shape the future where you can create, drive, build, and be a part of improving innovative energy solutions, while achieving your personal career goals. We prioritize work-life balance with flexible working hours, remote work options, and over 7 weeks of paid time off.\n\nWe foster a creative and inclusive culture, emphasizing diversity and equality. We are dedicated to our employees\' well-being, offering opportunities to join various social activity clubs, ranging from yoga and fishing to creative clubs.\n\nIn 2027, we will consolidate our Zealand locations into one large site in Trekroner, Roskilde.\n\nAbout Everllence\n\nEverllence, formerly known as MAN Energy Solutions, is a leading provider of propulsion, decarbonization and e