cture and practices of a fast-growing platform \nCentral Copenhagen office ‚Äì Join our new team in a modern office just steps away from everything the city has to offer as well as public transportation \nStrong foundation, startup feel ‚Äì Aspire is our youngest Defence product with strong adoption and more to come \nInternational, collaborative culture ‚Äì Work alongside skilled teams in Aarhus, Bucharest, and beyond \n\n\n\nYour Qualifications \nBeyond your experience ‚Äì that you see below ‚Äì we like to put emphasis on who you are as a person. We hope to meet someone who is able to communicate well and would like to share your thoughts and ideas while at the same time contribute to a strong team culture in the new team in Copenhagen.\n\nBachelors or Masters degree within Software Engineering or related field \n+2 years of experience from a similar full time position \nJava/Kotlin and Spring \nBuild/deployment pipelines \nExperience with Azure or other cloud provider platforms \n\n\n\nFurthermore, experience with Angular, Typescript, scripting in Bash/PowerShell, DevOps, building and deploying services, relational databases and Keycloak‚ÄØas well as deployment automation is beneficial.\n\n Please note‚ÄØthat you must be able to present a clean criminal record and have lived in a NATO/EU country for the past seven years as we work with security-classified projects. Read more‚ÄØhere. \n\nWelcome to Systematic Copenhagen \nWhen you join us in Copenhagen, you\'re not just getting a desk at one of the city‚Äôs best locations‚Äîyou‚Äôre stepping into a workplace where community matters. Our Employees Club keeps things lively with monthly social events, and our office catering makes sure you‚Äôre always well taken care of. Whether you‚Äôre into casual games or just good company, you‚Äôll find both at our foosball table or during our relaxed Friday bar gatherings.\n\nNever stop developing \nSystematic is uniquely people-centric, truly international and proudly rooted in