-01 10:27:36'),(482,4243807730,'Senior Software Specialist',223,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nWood Thilsted is a purpose-driven company, delivering engineering consultancy services to speed the global energy transition and to deliver well-being to our employees. We have been consistently successful in attracting the most competent and experienced design specialists, passionate about working in the global wind industry. Our team of world-class engineers delivers innovative, sustainable and optimised solutions that empower clients to achieve their renewable energy goals with greater speed and efficiency.\n\nOur team of world-class engineers delivers innovative, sustainable and optimised solutions that empower clients to achieve their renewable energy goals with greater speed and efficiency. We operate globally, supporting projects located in Asia, North America and Northern Europe. We currently employ a staff of over 180, most based in the UK and Denmark but also in offices in Taiwan, Japan, Poland and the USA with a continued growth foreseen in the near future.\n\nWe are now searching for a highly capable Senior Software Specialist in our Software and Tools Development Team. As a Senior Software Specialist, you will play a crucial role in developing and maintaining our in-house software packages, as well as interfaces to other engineering tools. Innovation through automation is at the core of how we work, so you should have the ambition to push boundaries and build smarter, faster workflows. Your work will directly impact the performance, accuracy, and usability of our in-house tools used by our engineers. This role is open in Denmark and our offices within this region are Copenhagen, Vejle, and Aarhus.\n\nAreas of Responsibility:\n\nSoftware Development\n\n\nDesign, develop, and maintain engineering software tools using MATLAB and Python, focusing on numerical methods, scientific computing, and optimization. \nDevelop and integrate algorithms to support advanced simulation and data analysis. \nDevelop automated workflows and associated documentation, e.g. parameterized LaTeX reports as well as result visualization (model exchange via web interfaces)\n\n\nInfrastructure & DevOps\n\n\nBuild and implement DevOps/ CICD pipelines‚ÄØto streamline software development and deployment. \nContribute to scaling and maintaining our in-house HPC cluster using Docker, Kubernetes, and HTCondor, with potential cloud integration. \n\n\nCollaboration & Support\n\n\nWork closely with IT to ensure software infrastructure and deployment environments are aligned and fully supported. \nProvide technical support and mentorship to engineering teams using our tools. \n\n\nInnovation & Automation\n\n\nIntegrate AI/ML capabilities, including Large Language Models (LLMs), into workflows to enhance decision-making and process automation. \nDevelop interfaces with SQL and PostgreSQL databases for efficient data management and system integration. \n\n\nYour Background:\n\nRequired:\n\n\nMSc or PhD in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, Physics, or a related technical discipline. \nStrong proficiency in MATLAB and Python, particularly for numerical modelling and scientific computing. \nExperience with Git/GitHub for version control, automated workflows, and collaborative software development. \nUnderstanding of CICD practices and DevOps principles. \nStrong analytical skills and a problem-solving mindset. \n\n\nPreferred:\n\n\nFamiliarity with machine learning and AI tools and working knowledge of Large Language Models (LLMs) such as OpenAI or Hugging Face. \nExperience with LaTeX for typesetting \nExperience working with both SQL and PostgreSQL databases. \nExcellent communication skills and ability to collaborate across teams and technical disciplines. \n\n\nIn return, we offer you excellent opportunities to influence your daily work, develop new competences, and work on interesting projects. At Wood Thilsted, we care about