hat design and implement the solutions but at the same time are responsible for quality and deadlines. We have a user centric mind-set that enables us to keep track of details while ensuring that the end-user is provided with an intuitive and easily accessible solution.\n\n\n\n\nYour tasks will primarily be to:\n\n\n\n\nDesign and implement new functionality.\nOptimize and develop our existing solutions.\nArchitectural and interface definitions in teams of 2-12 developers.\nDevelop unit and integration tests.\nReview the code written by your colleagues.\nSystem test in simulated environments and on full radar systems.\nOur technical environment consists of Visual Studio C++/C#, .NET6, Git and Azure DevOps.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nExperience across Windows applications\n\nYou have experience with C++ or C# development, preferably with Windows applications for configuration and control. Furthermore, it is an advantage if you have an interest in mathematics and/ or physic because it is the cornerstone of our systems.\n\n\n\n\nYour professional CV comprises:\n\n\n\n\nA university degree within engineering.\nGood programming skills in C++ or C#.\nExperience with DevOps.\nKnowledge of parallel programming.\nGood communication skills in English both written and spoken.\n\n\n\n\nWe do not expect you to have radar knowledge. The most important thing is that you are motivated for a steep learning curve, then we have a tailored introduction ready for you.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nYour new team\n\nThe team consists of 12 highly competent and dedicated colleagues, and we work closely together with the rest of Weibel‚Äôs software teams with approximately 65 developers across the different teams. We are a part of Weibel‚Äôs Technology department where you will join more than 195 engineering colleagues and together design and develop the best solutions for our customers. We have all of our development and production in-house and our engineering competencies spans across many technical fields such as system engineering, mechanical, electrical, hardware, software and technical design.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nContact and application\n\nApply through our website using the ‚ÄùApply‚Äù button. You can send your resum√© in Danish or English, and it is not a requirement that you attach a cover letter. If you have any questions, please reach out to Application Software manager, Jakob Seedorff on jas@weibel.dk.\n\n\n\n\nThe deadline is August 4th, 2025.\n\n\n\n\nPlease be aware that it is a requirement for this position that you can provide a criminal record with no remarks and obtain a security clearance.\n\n\n\n\nWe are looking forward to hearing from you.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4258453897/','2025-06-28',81,NULL,'[\"C\", \"C#\", \"C++\", \"Git\", \"OOP\", \"Programmering\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Softwareimplementering\", \"Testautomatisering\", \"Visual Studio\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:27:47','2025-07-01 10:27:47'),(485,4253314426,'Trouble Shooter Engineer',225,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nAt Alstom, we understand transport networks and what moves people. From high-speed trains, metros, monorails, and trams, to turnkey systems, services, infrastructure, signalling and digital mobility, we offer our diverse customers the broadest portfolio in the industry. Every day, 80 000 colleagues lead the way to greener and smarter mobility worldwide, connecting cities as we reduce carbon and replace cars.\n\nCould you be the full-time Troubleshooting Technician in Copenhagen we‚Äôre looking for?\n\nYour future role\n\nTake on a new challenge and apply your technical troubleshooting, investigation, and testing expertise in a new cutting-edge field. You‚Äôll work alongside dedicated and supportive teammates.\n\nYou\'ll provide crucial technical expertise to subcontractors, the warranty support team, and project team members, ensuring the availability of Alstom products. Day-to-day, you‚Äôll work closely with teams across the business (PI Support team