upplerende baggrund som elektriker.\nDu besidder erfaring med bygningsinstallationer generelt ‚Äì herunder lys- og kraftinstallationer, ABA og eventuelt CTS.\nDu har opdateret viden om elinstallationer samt projektering i henhold til DS/HD 60364.\n\n\nDu er en holdspiller, der er god til at samarbejde og kommunikere b√•de mundtligt og skriftligt ‚Äì ogs√• p√• engelsk. Du kan arbejde selvst√¶ndigt med projekterne, herunder analysere kundernes behov og komme med konstruktive l√∏sninger. Du er l√∏sningsorienteret, omstillingsparat og har mod p√• at bidrage med dine egne input og gode id√©er til l√∏sning af konkrete problemstillinger. N√•r opgaverne er mange og udfordrende, mister du ikke overblikket.\n\nS√•dan kommer du videre Hvis du √∏nsker at vide mere om stillingen, dens mange muligheder og udfordringer samt om Sweco som arbejdsplads, er du velkommen til at kontakte teamleder Anne Meibom p√• mail: anne.meibom@sweco.dk. Brug venligst linket for at sende relevante dokumenter hurtigst muligt.\n\nTransforming Society Together\n\nSweco planl√¶gger og designer fremtidens b√¶redygtige samfund og byer. Med den samlede viden fra vores 22.000 arkitekter, ingeni√∏rer og andre eksperter, arbejder vi sammen med kunderne for at fremme den gr√∏nne omstilling, √∏ge potentialet fra digitalisering og styrke vores samfund.\n\nSweco er Europas f√∏rende arkitekt- og ingeni√∏rr√•dgiver med en oms√¶tning p√• 31 mia. SEK (2,7 mia. EUR) i 2024. Virksomheden er b√∏rsnoteret p√• Nasdaq Stockholm. www.swecogroup.com','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4124581626/','2025-06-26',29,NULL,'[\"CSS\", \"HTML\", \"Linux\", \"MySQL\", \"PHP\", \"Python\", \"jQuery\", \"El\", \"Ingeni√∏rarbejde\", \"Samarbejde\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:29:09','2025-07-01 10:29:09'),(509,4256342483,'RF and Mixed-signal IC Developer',48,'Lund, Sk√•ne len, Sverige','Om jobbet\n\nJoin our Team\n\nAbout This Opportunity\n\nWe are seeking a skilled analog/RF/Mixed-signal integrated circuit developer to join our dynamic RF&MS IC development team within PEU Silicon. Our mission is to create cutting-edge RF and Mixed-signal integrated circuit solutions for our radio products. As a key member of our team, you will be instrumental in designing and developing advanced RFICs and mixed-signal ICs, including data converters, for next-generation wireless communication systems. This role offers the opportunity to work on challenging projects and contribute to the success of Ericsson, the global leader in connectivity!\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\nIn this role, you will be responsible for developing and implementing cutting-edge RF and MS IC solutions for both product and pre-development projects.\n\nYou will work closely with technical leaders, project managers, and other stakeholders to understand requirements and translate them into circuit designs.\n\nYour work will be meticulously documented in accordance with our development process requirements, and you will actively participate in reviewing the work of others.\n\nYou will evaluate your designs at the device level through hands-on measurements in the lab, ensuring they meet specifications and simulation results.\n\nStaying current with industry trends and best practices in RF and MS IC design development is essential, and you will share your knowledge and experience with your colleagues.\n\nAdditionally, occasional travel to our other sites in Sweden will be required.\n\nThe Skills You Bring\n\nWe are looking for a candidate with a Master\'s or Ph.D. in Electrical Engineering and at least six years of industry experience in a similar role.\n\nThe ideal candidate will have a comprehensive understanding of the full end-to-end design cycle in RF or MS IC development, along with in-depth knowledge of analog, RF, and mixed-signal circuit design theory, methods, and tools.\n\nExperience with sub-20nm technologies for integrated circuit design and lab measurements on manufactured devices is essential.\n\nStrong problem-solving and communication skills are a must, as well as a mindset geared towards continuous self-development and curiosity for future roles.\n\nThe candidate should be focused on team goals and results, capable of making courageous decisions even with incomplete information, and able to collaborate effectively in cross-site teams.\n\nFluency in English is required.\n\nMeriting Qualifications\n\n\n Experience from Power Amplifier development in CMOS /GaN technologies\n Experience from high-performance analog-to-digital or digital-to-analog converter design\n Experience in high-level modelling tools and programming languages for IC sub-systems\n Experience from FinFet process technologies\n Driving technical development as a technical leader\n\n\nApplication\n\nWe look forward to your application with CV in English. We target 60% work-from-the office.\n\nLast day to apply is 2nd July 2025. Please note that we do not accept, proceed, or respond for applications sent via e-mail.\n\nIf you have specific questions, you are welcome to contact Lovina Rebeiro, Sr. Talent Acquisition Partner at lovina.rebeiro@ericsson.com\n\nWhy join Ericsson?\n\nAt Ericsson, you¬¥ll have an outstanding opportunity. The chance to use your skills and imagination to push the boundaries of what¬¥s possible. To build solutions never seen before to some of the world‚Äôs toughest problems. You¬¥ll be challenged, but you won‚Äôt be alone. You¬¥ll be joining a team of diverse innovators, all driven to go beyond the status quo to craft what comes next.\n\nWhat happens once you apply?\n\nClick Here to find all you need to know about what our typical hiring process looks like.\n\nEncouraging a diverse and inclusive organization is core to our values at Ericsson, that\'s why we champion it in everything we do. We truly believe that by collaborating with people with different experiences we drive innovation, which is essential for our future growth. We encourage people from all backgrounds to apply and realize their full potential as part of our Ericsson team. Ericsson is proud to be an Equal Opportunity Employer. learn more.\n\nPrimary country and city: Sweden (SE) || Stockholm\n\nReq ID: 768491','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4256342483/','2025-06-26',17,NULL,'[\"Engelsk\", \"Programmering\", \"Converter\", \"Kommunikationssystemer\", \"Pre-development\", \"Probleml√∏sning\", \"RF\", \"Signal\", \"Technology Development\", \"Tr√•dl√∏s\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:29:14','2025-07-01 10:29:14'),(510,4256327045,'CTO',237,'Helsingborg, Sk√•ne len, Sverige','Om jobbet\n\n√Ñr du utvecklaren som vill ta n√§sta steg - utan att sl√§ppa det tekniska?\n\nHos oss f√•r du s√§tta den tekniska riktningen p√• riktigt. Vi bygger system som anv√§nds f√∂r att hantera ekonomisk f√∂rvaltning i komplexa organisationer; som kommunala och privata fastighetsbolag och andra verksamheter som beh√∂ver stabilitet, sp√•rbarhet och skalbarhet. V√•r kod har livsl√§ngd och just nu √§r vi mitt i en moderniseringsresa d√§r du f√•r leda tekniken.\n\nDet h√§r √§r inte en roll d√§r du bara sitter i m√∂ten. Du kommer fortfarande skriva kod, fatta arkitekturbeslut och v√§lja verktyg ‚Äì men du g√∂r det med inflytande. Du s√§tter riktningen. Du f√•r s√§ga \"vi ska fasa ut det gamla\", och sedan faktiskt g√∂ra det.\n\nDu jobbar n√§ra ett engagerat team och har fullt mandat att v√§lja hur vi bygger vidare: molnstrategi, CI/CD, s√§kerhet, datamodell ‚Äì allt. H√§r finns inget ramverk som √§r \"beslutat n√•gon annanstans\". H√§r √§r det du som leder det tekniska arbetet, fr√•n id√© till implementation.\n\nVem s√∂ker vi?\n\nVi tror att du:\n\n\n Har fler√•rig- och bred erfarenhet som utvecklare och mjukvaruarkitekt, g√§rna med bakgrund fr√•n .NET-milj√∂er.\n Har arbetat med modernisering av √§ldre system och har f√∂rst√•else f√∂r b√•de m√∂jligheter och fallgropar.\n √Ñr van vid att fatta tekniska beslut och leda andra, formellt eller informellt.\n Har god f√∂rst√•else f√∂r infrastruktur, DevOps och molntj√§nster.\n Har ett strategiskt t√§nk och kan oms√§tta aff√§rsm√•l till tekniska initiativ.\n √Ñr prestigel√∂s, nyfiken och trivs i ett mindre bolag med stort ansvar.\n √Ñr flytande i svenska och engelska i tal och skrift\n Extra plus om du har arbetat med informationss√§kerhet, regelefterlevnad eller SaaS-l√∂sningar med m√•nga kunder..\n\n\nVad vi erbjuder\n\nHos Akribi blir du en del av ett l√∂nsamt och stabilt bolag i tillv√§xtfas, med kunder som g√∂r verklig samh√§llsnytta. Du f√•r en central roll med stort inflytande √∂ver teknikval, arbetss√§tt och framtida v√§gval. Vi √§r ett tight team som st√∂ttar varandra och v√§xer tillsammans, och hos oss blir du lyssnad p√•, b√•de vad g√§ller kodbasen och runt ledningsbordet. Vi erbjuder konkurrenskraftig l√∂n och bra f√∂rm√•ner. Dessutom har vi flexibla arbetstider och hybridarbete.\n\nSedan 2022 √§r vi en del av Nordtech Group, en v√§xande familj av nordiska mjukvarubolag som delar en gemensam vision: att skapa h√•llbara och l√•ngsiktiga digitala l√∂sningar som verkligen g√∂r skillnad f√∂r v√•ra kunder. Som en del av Nordtech f√•r vi b√•de styrkan i en st√∂rre grupp och friheten att forts√§tta utvecklas p√• v√•rt s√§tt - n√§ra kunderna och med stort fokus p√• v√•ra medarbetare.\n\nV√§lkommen med din ans√∂kan!\n\nPlaceringsort f√∂r rollen √§r v√•rt fina huvudkontor i Oceanhamnen i Helsingborg, och vi ser fram emot att v√§lkomna dig till v√•rt team! Vi intervjuar l√∂pande efter semestrarna s√• v√§nta inte med att skicka in din ans√∂kan.\n\nI denna rekryteringsprocess till√§mpar vi psykometriska tester fr√•n Alva Labs. Anledningen till det √§r f√∂r att s√§kerst√§lla att vi ger dig, och andra kandidater, en r√§ttvis chans att visa sin l√§mplighet f√∂r rollen :)','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4256327045/','2025-06-26',NULL,NULL,'[\"Cloud computing\", \"Java\", \"Linux\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Webtjenester\", \"IT-strategi\", \"Informationssikkerhed\", \"Nedarvede systemer\", \"SaaS\", \"Svensk\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:29:19','2025-07-01 10:29:19');
INSERT INTO `job_postings` VALUES (511,4131126092,'Senior Software Engineer',238,'Malm√∏, Sk√•ne len, Sverige','Om jobbet\n\n\"At Klipboard we\'ve introduced a flexible hybrid work policy, where employees spend three days in the office and two days working from home. This approach promotes a balanced work environment that combines office collaboration with the comfort and convenience of remote work.\"\n\nKlipboard provides specialist software, services and support to deliver fully integrated trading and business management solutions to companies in the distributive trade ‚Äì wherever they are in the world. With a unique depth of knowledge and experience in ERP/SaaS solutions, Klipboard has a wide range of clients includes wholesalers, distributors, merchants and retailers from small traders to multinational enterprises. Klipboard has offices in the UK, Ireland, The Netherlands, South Africa, Kenya and North America. Our mission is simple: to design and deliver high performance, integrated ERP solutions that enable our distributive trade customers to source effectively, stock efficiently, sell profitably and service competitively\n\nWe are seeking a highly skilled Senior Software Engineer with expertise in C# .NET, .NET Core, GIT to join our dynamic team. In this role, you will actively contribute to hands-on coding, guiding the technical direction of your squad, and troubleshooting complex issues. You‚Äôll lead by example, ensuring the rapid and efficient delivery of high-quality software solutions into production. You\'ll be instrumental in driving a fast-paced team that continuously optimises processes for speed and efficiency without compromising quality. Contribute to code reviews and provide constructive feedback to more junior members of the team.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n\nExcited about being part of a fast-growing company that‚Äôs trying to make a positive change for the customers it serves.\nKnows how to have fun whilst maintaining a professional outlook.\nGenuine interest in SaaS technology.\nA driven, ambitious self-starter.\nLearning mindset and motivated to develop skills further and keep up to date with emerging technologies.\nYou will be willing to share your technical knowledge and will contribute to an environment of continuous improvement.\n\n\nSoft Skills\n\nSkills, Knowledge and Experience:\n\n\nTeam player.\nWork experience (not necessarily in engineering).\nConstant learner (ready to embrace new processes/technology/work culture).\n\n\nEngineeringskills\n\n\nGIT.\nC# .NET .NET Core.\nBlazer / MVC / WinForms.\nUnit testing.\nWeb application security.\n\n\nLanguage and location\n\n\nBased in Sweden (Malm√∂) \nFluent in Swedish or English.\n\n\nMerits\n\n\nAndroid development (MAUI / Kotlyn)\nMore than 5 years of software engineering experience with the last few years in a senior capacity.\nExperience in CI / CD.\nExperience building cloud native applications.\nExperience using Docker.\nPossess some experience of mentoring and lead small project teams \n\n\nCompany Info\n\nYou may also have seen from our recent posts that we are excited to begin sharing our new company name ‚Äì Klipboard. Kerridge Commercial Systems (KCS) is becoming Klipboard and our new brand is designed to bring together our expertise across distribution, automotive, retail, rental, transport management, manufacturing, and field service management. We have offices based across the world and we are looking for talented individuals to join our growing teams. Due to our growth over the last few years it is an exciting time to join us as we enter our next chapter! At Klipboard we\'ve introduced a flexible hybrid work policy, where employees spend three days in the office and two days working from home. This approach promotes a balanced work environment that combines office collaboration with the comfort and convenience of remote work.\"\n\nEqual Opportunities\n\nAs a global company, we value and respect the diversity of our workforce, aiming to empower everyone to embrace each other\'s differences. We are committed to creating an inclusive workplace where diversity, equity, and inclusion are integral to our company and culture. We recognize the benefits of a diverse workforce, where creativity and valuing differences enable us all to thrive and sparks innovation.\n\nIf you require any help, adjustments and/or support during the interview and offer process then please advise our TA or HR team.\n\nResearch shows that women and other underrepresented groups are less likely to apply for a role unless they meet every listed requirement. However, we recognise that skills and experience come in many forms, and we encourage you to apply even if you don‚Äôt meet every criterion. If you are passionate about this role and believe you have the right mindset and transferrable skills, we would love to hear from you!\n\nTo all recruitment agencies: Klipboard does not accept agency speculative resumes. At present we only accept CV‚Äôs from Agencies on our PSL who have been assigned specific position/s. Please do not forward resumes to our careers site or direct to Klipboard employee as this does not constitute an introduction and Klipboard retrospectively will not be liable for any candidate ownership or fees related to unsolicited resumes.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4131126092/','2025-06-26',100,NULL,'[\".NET\", \"C#\", \"JavaScript\", \"OOP\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \".NET Core\", \"Bl√∏de kompetencer\", \"Kode-gennemgang\", \"Projektteams\", \"XML\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:29:21','2025-07-01 10:29:21'),(512,4133026922,'Senior Software Developer - develop features for growing library solution',50,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nSenior Software Developer ‚Äì develop features for growing library solution\n\nCan you check off the following:\n Experienced software developer. Have a keen eye for designing features. Enjoy responsibility. Can drive new product development. Then you are the one we are looking for.\n\nHaving responsibility and paving the way for new initiatives\nAs our new colleague, your primary responsibility will be leading feature development.\n\nIn addition to that, some of your key tasks will be to:\n\n\nDrive design, discuss and implement solutions for new features,\nEnsure code review and inspection,\nBe a role model when it comes to coding, facilitation and conducting scrum,\nParticipate in knowledge sharing and sparring with other developers\n\n\n\nJoin a growing team working with a library solutions for Germany and the Nordics\nOur department is growing and we are, therefore, looking for colleagues in Copenhagen. In cooperation with our committed and highly skilled group of 25 colleagues, comprising domain experts and developers, placed in Aarhus, Copenhagen, and Bucharest, you will accelerate the development and improvement of our library and learning product suite, Cicero. \n\nCicero is used in public libraries and schools in every Danish municipality and at 300+ schools in Sweden, now growing into the German and Norwegian market as well. Cicero was built to support library workers in their daily work and ensure that all libraries in the country work in synergy.\n\nBring Your Experience Into Play\nWe are looking for someone, who will enjoy working in a team with colleagues with different technical capabilities and are able to bring that into play. Furthermore, you enjoy being a part of a team and contribute to the daily life in the office, while at the same time contributing to a good team culture. You also thrive in a team where some of the team members are located remotely calling for online collaboration.\n\nWe expect that you have:\n\n\nBachelor‚Äôs or Master‚Äôs degree in computer science, software engineering, or similar\n+5 years of experience as a software developer \n\n\n\nIn terms of technologies, we are looking for some with a solid technical foundation in the following:\n\n\nJava\nIntelliJ or Eclipse\nSQL\n\n\n\nIf you have dabbled with PostgreSQL, GitLab, MQ, Docker and Kubernetes, Angular and TeamCity, this will be an advantage ‚Äì not a requirement.\n\nIn the first period of your employment, you should expect travel activity to our HQ in Aarhus where we will make sure that you receive a great onboarding ‚Äì both to Systematic but also to how we develop our software.\n\nPlease note that you must be able to present a clean criminal record and have lived in a NATO/EU country for the past seven years as some of Systematic‚Äôs projects are security-classified. Read more here.\n\nWelcome to Systematic Copenhagen \nWhen you join us in Copenhagen, you\'re not just getting a desk at one of the city‚Äôs best locations‚Äîyou‚Äôre stepping into a workplace where community matters. Our Employees Club keeps things lively with monthly social events, and our office catering makes sure you‚Äôre always well taken care of. Whether you‚Äôre into casual games or just good company, you‚Äôll find both at our foosball table or during our relaxed Friday bar gatherings.\n\nNever stop developing\nSystematic is uniquely people-centric, truly international and proudly rooted in Denmark with more than 1100 employees. Together, we write intelligent and innovative code to drive progress and improve lives. We develop IT solutions that make a real difference where it matters most. This is why we never stop developing. Here, there is room to be professional and personal. It is not just a place to work but a place to belong. \n\nStart your development here \nWe will be assessing applications on an ongoing basis as we wish to welcome our new colleague as soon as possible, so click Apply Now and send us your CV today. If you have any questions, you are always welcome to contact us on tel. +45 8943 2000 and ask for Kathrine Schlegel Rasmussen, Senior TA Consultant or Poul Dam Bangsund, Senior Project Manager.\n\nGet in touch\n\nKathrine Schlegel Rasmussen\n\nSenior Talent Acquisition Consultant','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4133026922/','2025-06-26',100,NULL,'[\"Datalogi\", \"Git\", \"Java\", \"JavaScript\", \"Kubernetes\", \"OOP\", \"Scrum\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Facilitering\", \"XML\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:29:25','2025-07-01 10:29:25'),(513,4256672388,'Godt job med lange vagter hos ung mand i R√∏dovre',81,'R√∏dovre, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nVil du arbejde i lange vagter, og vil du v√¶re respiratorisk handicaphj√¶lper for en yngre mand i R√∏dovre? S√• l√¶s med her!\n\nOm opgaven\n\nSimon er 30 √•r og bor for sig selv i R√∏dovre. Til dagligt studerer han kommunikation p√• CBS og laver bestyrelsesarbejde som frivillig i Kr√¶ftens Bek√¶mpelse og Danske Handicaporganisationer.\n\nSimon er udadvendt og bruger meget tid med familie og venner. Mad og hyggelige aftener ude i byen med venner betyder meget for Simon, s√• i perioder skal man v√¶re klar p√• at sidde for sig selv og v√¶re til r√•dighed, hvis han har brug for hj√¶lp andre steder end i hjemmet. Andre gange tager Simon til koncerter eller p√• bar, hvor musikken og den festlige stemning, g√∏r, at man skal v√¶re mere p√•.\n\nInden alle ture har han gjort det til en vane at tjekke ind, s√• han og hj√¶lper ved, hvad der skal ske, og hvordan.\n\nN√•r Simon er hjemme sidder han typisk ved sin computer og spiller, arbejder eller ser film, og de tidspunkter p√• dagen, hvor der bliver lavet rutine opgaver, eller der bliver k√∏rt bil, kan han godt lide at snakke og grine.\n\nFor Simon er det vigtigt at have en t√¶t relation til sine hj√¶lpere, s√• man skal v√¶re klar p√• en snak, og man skal kunne og kunne tage imod ris og ros. Det g√¶lder ogs√• den anden vej.\n\nSimon sidder i k√∏restol og styrer sin k√∏restol med munden.\n\nSimon har fuldt sprog, benytter respirator, og har brug for praktisk hj√¶lp i hjemmet, personlig pleje, respiratorisk overv√•gning samt ledsagelse til hans uddannelsessted, CBS.\n\nVi s√∏ger en respiratorisk handicaphj√¶lper, der leder efter et fast job evt. efter endt studie