benhavn NV med mulighed for hjemmearbejde\nEn v√¶rdibaseret arbejdsplads med h√∏j arbejdsgl√¶de og tydelige resultater\nMening! Og mulighed for at s√¶tte tydelige aftryk i indsamlingen til hospitalsklovnenes arbejde for syge og s√•rbare b√∏rn\n\n\n\nAns√∏gning\n\nSend din ans√∏gning og CV senest 3. august. Har du sp√∏rgsm√•l, er du velkommen til at kontakte fundraisingchef Malene Berland Grauslund p√• malene@danskehospitalsklovne.dk eller 22 20 34 72.\n\nVi forventer at afholde f√∏rste samtaler 11.-12. august og eventuelt anden samtale 21. august.\n\nDanske Hospitalsklovne √∏nsker at afspejle det samfund, vi er en del af, og vi opfordrer alle kvalificerede kandidater til at s√∏ge ‚Äì uanset alder, k√∏n, etnicitet, religion mv.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4257407008/','2025-06-26',NULL,NULL,'[\"Budgettering\", \"Driftsledelse\", \"Eventplanl√¶gning\", \"Events\", \"Fundraising\", \"Inspiration\", \"Kommunikation\", \"Legatudformning\", \"Marketing\", \"Pr√¶stationsmarketing\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:29:36','2025-07-01 10:29:36'),(516,4249955446,'CTO, Head of Technology Strategy',240,'Kongens Lyngby, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nDo you envision yourself crafting the future of premium sound and timeless design by transformative innovations in a company known for redefining the audio-visual industry for almost 100 years? Are you ready to accept the challenge of leveraging advanced technology to create timeless, luxurious experiences?\n\nAs CTO, Head of Technology Strategy, you will join the Product Creation Management Team at Bang & Olufsen, reporting directly to our COO. In this forward-thinking leadership position, you will oversee and shape our technology strategy across product, embedded systems, cloud solutions, software platforms, hardware, and innovation initiatives. You will be instrumental in guiding B&O‚Äôs approach to developing innovative sound experiences that marry technology with design and skillful craftsmanship.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n\n\n Craft Bang & Olufsen‚Äôs long-term technology strategy by working closely with the COO.\n Guide architecture and platform decisions to support our pillars: Luxury, Timeless, Technology.\n Engage and build partnerships with key external technology collaborators around the world.\n Develop and implement innovation frameworks that facilitate groundbreaking product development.\n Explore and adopt new technologies to ensure B&O\'s leadership in premium consumer electronics.\n Serve as a bridge between engineering and executive leadership to align technological direction with business outcomes.\n Represent Bang & Olufsen in external forums and partnerships, building a global voice for technology excellence.\n\n\n\nWhat You Bring\n\nYou are a visionary and involved leader with profound knowledge of elegant technology solutions, embedded platforms, real-time systems, and audio innovation. You balance strategic thinking with pragmatic execution and are skilled at communicating with technical and non-technical stakeholders.\n\nMoreover, you bring:\n\n\n\n Demonstrated leadership in a senior technical role within premium consumer electronics or related industries.\n Deep knowledge of electronics, product development, embedded software (C++, Linux, Yocto, FreeRTOS, Zephyr), cloud integration, quality, system design.\n Experience with full product development lifecycles and platform strategy.\n A track record of leading innovation and bringing next-generation technology to market.\n Proficient in providing strategic guidance that resonates with C-suite executives.\n Clear and compelling communication and storytelling ability.\n An innovative mindset that supports progressive ideas and new approaches.\n\n\n\nWhat We Offer\n\nYou will collaborate with some of the most innovative thinkers in product, design, and engineering as we shape the future of luxury audio. You will partner with our executive leadership to define technology direction, inspire a shared vision, and enhance product excellence.\n\nWith approximately 1,100 employees, Bang & Olufsen is an agile company that gives room for individual flexibility and decision-making. Our hierarchy is flat, and our communication is open and trustworthy. Our culture emphasizes respect for one another, as we leverage the diverse perspectives of our team from over 55 countries to cultivate an inclusive workplace that promotes our shared development - individually and collectively as a brand.\n\nCompensation: Competitive salary and benefits package\n\nLocation: Struer or Kongens Lyngby, Denmark (Flexible with regular visits to Denmark)\n\nStart date: As soon as possible\n\nTravel: Approx. 20% (depending on your location)\n\nHow To Apply\n\nSubmit your CV and application in English by pressing the ‚ÄòApply‚Äô button. Applications are assessed continuously, so please apply as soon as possible.\n\nAt Bang & Olufsen, we believe in equal opportunities for all. We encourage applicants to focus on their qualifications, skills, and experience when submitting their CVs. Please refrain from including personal information such as photographs. Our hiring decisions are based solely on merit, and we are committed to creating a diverse and inclusive workplace where everyone has the opportunity to thrive. If you see yourself in the position and believe you have the potential to support build B&O\'s future, even if you don\'t meet all the requirements, we sincerely encourage you to apply. We look forward to hearing from you!\n\nIf you want to know more about the position, you are welcome to contact our Senior TA Consultant, Antoniya Petkov on ANTP@bang-olufsen.dk . Please do not send your CV and application to this e-mail directly as these will not be taken into consideration.\n\nRead more about our recruitment process and explore your career opportunities within Bang & Olufsen here .\n\nBang & Olufsen has, for 100 years, developed luxury audio products that change moods and inspire minds. With offices in Denmark (headquartered in Struer) and the rest of the world, Bang & Olufsen is determined to create products that push the boundaries of audio technology. To this day, every product is still characterized by the unique combination of beautiful sound, timeless design and unrivalled craftmanship.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4249955446/','2025-06-26',100,NULL,'[\"Cloud computing\", \"Linux\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Webtjenester\", \"IT-strategi\", \"Produktudvikling\", \"Strategi\", \"Strategisk t√¶nkning\", \"Systemdesign\", \"Zephyr\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:29:39','2025-07-01 10:29:39'),(517,4045845180,'DevOps Specialist',51,'K√∏benhavns Kommune, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nWanna make an impact by driving DevOps transformation in a fast-growing software company?\n\nYour new role\n\nBy joining the Developer Enablement team at Dalux, you will be an essential part in enhancing the developer experience and our productivity as we scale up. You will be part of building and maintaining our CI/CD pipelines, and surrounding infrastructure, as well as spreading best practices of DevOps and general software engineering.\n\nYour responsibilities will include:\n\n\n Continuously work to improve Development in Dalux by sharing and implementing new ideas including evolving our systems to best serve the needs of our developers \n Clarify requirements and discuss specific technical and architectural solutions together with team members \n Coaching and training end-users (our developers) in using the platforms we provide \n Release and maintain components and internal products as needed \n Research and experimentation to determine opportunities for technical improvements \n\n\nOur tech stack includes:\n\n\n Jenkins (Jenkins Pipelines, JCasC) \n GitLab and Nexus (self-hosted) \n Docker \n Hyper-V \n Prometheus, Thanos and Grafana \n MSBuild \n NPM (pnpm and Vite) \n AWS (EC2, Elastic Beanstalk, CloudFormation, S3 etc.) \n\n\nWe aim to have reliable, repeatable, highly automated, build pipelines, configured as code. Shared and customized build systems serve a variety of teams from mobile, webapps, image processing, to backend services.\n\nOur builds and test are orchestrated using Jenkins and our code is hosted in Gitlab. The platforms are Linux and Windows.\n\nDalux‚Äô continuous growth makes the environment exciting and ever changing, but is also one of the reasons why our DevOps discipline is behind where we would like it to be.\n\nTo supplement our Developer Enablement team, we have a large DevOps guild helping with implementing best practices and sharing experiences across Dalux. Our development is characterized by a very pragmatic agile methodology with frequent releases. We apply the same pragmatism to DevOps and once value is demonstrated we are able to implement changes with great success.\n\nYour background\n\nWe expect that you have an educational background in Software Engineering. In addition, you have either been part of driving DevOps transformations previously and see DevOps as your strongest asset or tried DevOps a bit and are willing to learn it more deeply ‚Äì we have open positions for both options.\n\nWhat To Expect As a Daluxian\n\nDalux is a company built by engineers for engineers. Approximately half of our staff works within our development department. You will become part of a highly skilled team of passionate individuals driven by the wish to explore new and reshape existing technologies. We value our flat organizational structure, making the jump from idea to action swift with the best idea leading the way. We believe in straightforward and honest communication, trust in our employees, and making room for individual preferences.\n\nReady for the next step?\n\nIf we have managed to pique your interest, we would love to hear from you. Either send us an application or reach out to Nicole Przybylski for more information at np@dalux.com .\n\nWho is Dalux?\n\nDalux is a Danish software company founded in 2005 by Ph.D. Bent Dalgaard and Torben Dalgaard. Dalux‚Äô products are aimed at making the construction industry smarter and more effective. Our user-friendly digital tools and Building Information Modelling-technology (also known as BIM) is used in more than 140 countries globally.\n\nWe are crazy about cool technology and have experience being first movers on new tech. Our products are based on our unique 3D BIM-technology and makes use of AR - all developed entirely by Dalux.\n\nFor the last 8 years, we have grown by 50% annually. Dalux employs more than 550 employees distributed across 36 offices in 22 countries. All our product development is located in our offices in √òsterbro, Copenhagen.\n\nApplication deadline:\n\nAs soon as possible','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4045845180/','2025-06-26',100,NULL,'[\"DevOps\", \"Git\", \"Jenkins\", \"Kubernetes\", \"Linux\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Coaching og mentorarbejde\", \"Nexus\", \"Testautomatisering\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:29:42','2025-07-01 10:29:42'),(518,4257276330,'Business Central Developer',241,'Herlev Kommune, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nEr du en skarp Business Central Developer med solid erfaring i AL, og br√¶nder du for at levere kvalitetsrige l√∏sninger? Motiveres du samtidig af muligheden for at specialisere dig og dykke ned i komplekse tekniske udfordringer? I takt med vores fortsatte v√¶kst, s√∏ger vi en kompetent og erfaren udvikler til vores ECIT Consulting selskab, der vil v√¶re med til at styrke vores team og bidrage til udviklingen af skr√¶ddersyede l√∏sninger til vores kunder.\n\n\n\n\nVi leverer IT-l√∏sninger, men arbejder med mennesker\n\nVi tilbyder et job i et konsulenthus, der insisterer p√• ansvarlighed og ordentlighed over for b√•de dig som medarbejder og over for vores kunder. Det betyder, at vi behandler dig, hinanden og vores kunder med respekt, og at det er vigtigt for os, at du har en hverdag, hvor du f√∏ler dig b√•de udfordret og godt tilpas. Som medarb