ch Leader who wants to do high-leverage work with purpose, this is the opportunity you‚Äôve been waiting for.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nAbout this Opportunity\n\nAs Skatteguiden\'s CTO, you will lead the company‚Äôs technology strategy and execution, balancing long-term scalability with short-term delivery.\n\n\n\n\nYou will provide strategic vision, architectural direction, and hands-on leadership to a growing engineering team, driving innovation and operational excellence.\n\n\n\n\nYour focus will be on building a scalable, secure, and resilient platform, embedding core development principles, and fostering a high-performing engineering culture.\n\n\n\n\nYou will play a central role in evolving our platform architecture, ensuring robust security and compliance, and preparing the organisation for its next phase of growth.\n\n\n\n\nAs a key member of the management team, you will empower engineers, support expansion into new verticals, and help shape the company‚Äôs long-term technical direction.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nResponsibilities\n\nDefine and lead the company‚Äôs technology strategy, ensuring alignment with business vision and supporting both long-term scalability and short-term delivery\nDrive architectural direction and evolve the platform to support current and future demands, ensuring security, scalability, and efficiency\nBuild, mentor, and inspire high-performing, cross-functional engineering teams, fostering autonomy, knowledge sharing, and continuous learning\nOwn IT security, GDPR compliance, and environment separation, embedding robust security practices and readiness for standards like SOC 2\nCollaborate closely with management, Product, and Data to align technology initiatives with business objectives and support insight-driven decisions\nMaintain hands-on involvement in coding and troubleshooting, setting up the right team structure for scale, and quickly resolving technical issues. Notable tech stack is Java (Spring Boot), and React Native. \nPromote a positive, solution-oriented mindset, encouraging innovation, continuous improvement, and hypothesis-driven experimentation\nImplement and optimise automated infrastructure and user journey processes, enhancing operational efficiency and platform maturity\nBalance strategic vision with practical execution, making informed decisions, avoiding technical shortcuts, and adapting quickly to changing priorities\nBe available to respond to critical issues outside of standard hours, ensuring system reliability, uptime, and a resilient technical setup\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nYour Experience\n\nProven experience leading and scaling engineering teams from early-stage to growth (ideally in SaaS or product-led companies), including scaling from around 10 to 30+ engineers\nStrong strategic mindset with the ability to balance long-term scalability and short-term delivery, and embed core development principles\nHands-on technical expertise, comfortable diving into code and setting up scalable, modular architectures\nDemonstrated success in building secure, automated infrastructure, improving IT security (including GDPR compliance and environment separation), and readiness for standards like SOC 2\nExperience fostering a positive, high-performing team culture that encourages autonomy, ownership, and knowledge sharing\nAbility to communicate effectively with engineers and management, and collaborate with Product, Data, and other teams\nTrack record of making informed decisions quickly, balancing delivery speed with architectural discipline, and adapting to fast-paced environments\nPrevious roles such as Head of Tech, Director of Tech, or similar leadership positions in dynamic, growth-focused companies (preferably from fintech, SaaS, or tech startups)\nWillingness to be available beyond standard hours when critical issues arise, ensuring reliability and uptime\nStrong interpersonal skills with a likeable, energetic personality that fits well within a mixed senior and junior team, and proven ability to attract, hire, and mentor senior engineers\nPassion for continuous learning, improvement, and experimentation, unafraid to take calculated risks and learn from mistakes\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nWhat\'s in it for you\n\nOpportunity to shape the technology vision and strategy of a fast-growing company entering new verticals\nDirect influence on platform architecture, engineering culture, and organisational structure\nWork closely with a talented, collaborative team of senior and junior engineers\nHigh degree of autonomy and ownership, with the ability to implement your ideas and drive real impact\nBe a key member of the management team, helping to set the direction for the next phase of growth\nExposure to modern technologies, scalable infrastructure, and best practices in security and compliance\nA dynamic, learning-focused environment where experimentation and innovation are encouraged\nCompetitive compensation and the chance to grow with the company as it scales internationally\nYou will be a part of the board meetings (5 across the year)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nOur Lean Recruitment Process\n\n30-minute screening call with our recruiter, Christian Payne\n1 hour Online meeting with Martin (CPO) and Nikolai (CEO)\n1-hour Onsite meeting with your future developer team, and Nikolai (CEO)\n\n\n\n\nIf you are ready to lead Skatteguiden‚Äôs technology vision and drive innovation in a dynamic environment, we want to hear from you. Please apply, and you will hear from us within a week.\n\nTake the next step in your career and join us as our new CTO.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\nRead to the end and curious about our tech stack? Here it is! üëá\n\nTech-stack (development, backend)\n\n* Java (Spring Boot)\n\n* Mysql\n\n* MongoDB\n\n* RabbitMQ\n\n* Docker\n\n* NodeJS\n\n* OpenAPI\n\n* S3 storage\n\n\n\n\nTech-stack (development, frontend)\n\n* React-Native\n\n* TypeScript\n\n* Redux RTX\n\n* Codepush\n\n\n\n\nTech-stack (operations)\n\n* Kubernetes\n\n* ArgoCD\n\n* Grafana\n\n* Prometheus\n\n* Promtail\n\n* Lok