u must be able to present a clean criminal record and have lived in a NATO/EU country for the past seven years as we work with security-classified projects. Read more‚ÄØhere. \n\n \n\nWelcome to Systematic Copenhagen \nWhen you join us in Copenhagen, you\'re not just getting a desk at one of the city‚Äôs best locations‚Äîyou‚Äôre stepping into a workplace where community matters. Our Employees Club keeps things lively with monthly social events, and our office catering makes sure you‚Äôre always well taken care of. Whether you‚Äôre into casual games or just good company, you‚Äôll find both at our foosball table or during our relaxed Friday bar gatherings.\n\nNever stop developing \nSystematic is uniquely people-centric, truly international and proudly rooted in Denmark with more than 1100 employees. Together, we write intelligent and innovative code to drive progress and improve lives. We develop IT solutions that make a real difference where it matters most. This is why we never stop developing. Here, there is room to be professional and personal. It is not just a place to work but a place to belong. \n\nStart your development here \nWe will be assessing applications on an ongoing basis as we wish to welcome our new colleague as soon as possible, so click Apply Now and send us your CV today. If you have any questions, you are always welcome to contact us on tel. +45 8943 2000 and ask for Kathrine Schlegel Rasmussen, Senior TA Consultant\n\nGet in touch\n\nKathrine Schlegel Rasmussen\n\nSenior Talent Acquisition Consultant','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4176491427/','2025-06-24',60,NULL,'[\"Angular\", \"DevOps\", \"Java\", \"JavaScript\", \"Software Systems Engineering\", \"Softwareudvikling\", \"Kotlin\", \"Microsoft Azure\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:31:16','2025-07-01 10:31:16'),(544,4223867476,'IT Supporter Trainee',254,'K√∏benhavn, Region Hovedstaden, Danmark','Om jobbet\n\nJob Description:\n\nAre you currently in the process of taking an IT Supporter education? Would you like an option to learn how an enterprise operates IT? Would you like to gain the practical skills that will benefit you in your education? \n\nOne of the most important aspects within IT is IT Support - we help our colleagues do what they‚Äôre best at, by resolving the IT issues they face. If you‚Äôve got the right mindset and know that you‚Äôre going to be an IT Supporter as part of your next step in your career, continue reading!\n\nAs an IT Supporter Trainee in Satair, you will join a team situated in Copenhagen, Singapore, Beijing, Hamburg, and the US. We provide IT Support to our colleagues in the business on a 24/7 basis, by following the sun. As we are the first step into IT, guiding colleagues and leading them to our experts is also a discipline we practice.\n\nThe position is located in Kastrup, Denmark, and it is a requirement for candidates to be able to work from the office on all days of the week.\n\nWhat the job is ...\n\nYour main responsibility is to support our colleagues in the business when they face IT issues or when they request our services. As IT Support is the first point of contact, the ambition to provide good customer service is a necessity and timely resolution is a must.\n\nBesides being involved in various incidents and service requests, you will of course be trained and you will experience first-hand how the IT Supporters in the team, work with the areas below:\n\n\n Basic and complex IT troubleshooting and how to, in the best way possible, resolve issues \n How printers are setup physically and in the backend (digitally) \n How we set up warehouse and office workstations \n What DHCP and DNS is and how and when we use it \n What LAN patching is and how and when we do it \n What Active Directory is, and how and when we use it \n What SAP ERP is and how we support it \n What IT Asset Life Cycle Management is and how we practice it \n What Mobile Device Management is and how we use it \n ITIL (IT Infrastructure Library) related processes and how we work within those processes \n How to support specific Satair applications \n The importance of communication, follow up and in general how we provide a world class customer service \n And many more exciting areas that will give you the practical experience that you need in your future career as an IT Supporter \n\n\nCentral aspects of the job:\n\n\n Supporting your colleagues with IT Incidents and Service Requests \n Assist our colleagues in Infrastructure & Operations on tasks where help is needed \n Purchase equipment and ensure asset management is done according to our processes \n Ensure that access administration activities are done with proper attention and care \n Using our knowledge articles to help you with resolving incidents and completing service requests \n Work closely with the different Service Desks within the organization of Airbus \n\n\nWhat do you offer?\n\nWe‚Äôre looking for a candidate who is on her or his way to become an IT Supporter. In addition you should like the IT Support aspect in terms of helping users and making sure that our colleagues have what was needed. Whatever skills that you don‚Äôt have today, we‚Äôre certain that you‚Äôll be able to gain during your trainee period in the Satair IT Support.\n\nAs a person, your default answer to something unknown should not be ,, I don‚Äôt know...‚Äô‚Äô but rather ,, I‚Äôll investigate and return!‚Äô‚Äô. In some cases, patience is required and you will need it.\n\n What are we looking for? How much experience? What type of experience? \n\n\n Currently undergoing education as an IT Supporter \n Takes pride in being reliable and punctual \n An interest in hardware, software, network, and communication tools. \n Fluent in English both written and verbally \n Written skills that demonstrates structure \n\n\nAbout SATAIR\n\nSatair is an Airbus Services company offering first-class material management solutions in the aviation aftermarket industry. We take pride in delive