andinavian comfort with a fast-paced, international mindset. With excellent transport connections and all the best the city has to offer right outside the door, it\'s the perfect base for doing great work ‚Äî and enjoying life while you do it. Come for the innovation, stay for the people.\n\n\n\n\nAbout Relax\n\nBack in 2010, we kicked off our journey with a simple mission - to create outstanding games for the modern iGaming world. Fast forward to today, and we\'ve grown to be one of the leading suppliers in the game, boasting an aggregation arm like no other. Despite our exponential growth, we\'ve succeeded in staying true to our core values throughout the years, these are to be: Driven, Adaptable, Supportive, and Respectful. We live and breathe this ethos across our offices across the globe, namely in Malta, Estonia, Serbia, Finland, Sweden, and Gibraltar. Keen to find out more? Learn about us here: https://relax-gaming.com/careers/life-at-relax.','https://www.linkedin.com/jobs/view/4233360750/','2025-06-24',21,NULL,'[\"C++\", \"Frontend-udvikling\", \"Brugeroplevelse\", \"Lederskab\", \"Online Poker\", \"Poker\", \"Synkronisering\", \"Teamlederskab\", \"Tr√•de\", \"iGaming\"]',NULL,'2025-07-01 10:32:23','2025-07-01 10:32:23'),(563,4222848827,'Senior Software Engineer (Golang/PHP) | Malm√∂',234,'Malm√∏, Sk√•ne len, Sverige','Om jobbet\n\nTHE OPPORTUNITY\n\nDo you believe that the only consistent thing in technology is change? If so, this position is for you!\n\nAt Boozt we are proud to say that we are a tech company at it\'s core and we are now looking for an experienced, self-motivated, and passionate GoLang developer to be part of our in-house team.\n\nOur Order and Return Management systems are developed in-house using a variety of technologies, PHP and Go being the main two. We practice engineering-driven business development and many important decisions are made by our developers. We do regular system maintenance to refactor and upgrade to the latest versions of components and libraries while doing our best to explore and incorporate new technologies and concepts. Our main focus is to be very close to the business units and users but we try to allow technology to guide us in how we make our choices.\n\nOur Medium Page\n\nWhat You Will Do\n\n\nImplement new features and functions needed for the company, when appropriate, have them be influenced by the use of AI and/or machine learning.\nMultiple deployments a day due to continuous integration and an agile workflow.\nAutomate manual tasks to help the business users do their everyday work.\nDevelopment and maintenance in Go.\nYou will interact with product managers and business unit representatives to help determine scopes, plan and specify projects.\nMaintaining and improving system integrations using asynchronous messaging (Google Pub/Sub, RabbitMQ and various APIs).\n\n\n\nYOUR PROFILE\n\n\nBroad experience from working with Go. Experience with PHP and Symfony is a plus.\nExperience with having used appropriate forms of AI for workflow improvements as well as incorporating it into projects or products in meaningful ways.\nExperience in working with other business units in order to understand the needs and improve the system.\nBS or MS degree in Computer Science or a related technical field is desirable.\nFluent in English since this is our corporate language (only applications in English will be considered)\n\n\n\nTechnical Keywords: Go, GoLang, AI, LLM, Machine Learning, PHP, Symfony, Google Cloud Platform, GitLab, Redis, RabbitMQ, PubSub, MySQL, CI/CD, DataDog, ElasticSearch, Manticore, Terraform, a mix of monolith and microservice solutions.\n\nBOOZT PERKS\n\n\nGreat personal and internal career development\nA culture that incorporates our values of trust, freedom, and responsibility\nFlexible work environment\nDriven and passionate international colleagues\nA generous employee discount\nWellness allowance and sports activities, HQ onsite masseuse and medical doctor\